title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix Pepperidge Farm corn meal stuffing, butter and broth.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in a baking dish.
Over this, add 1/2 cup onion and chopped celery.

title: waffle iron whoopie pies
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions, add flour and baking powder. Batter will be thick like waffles. Drop onto waffle iron. Watch carefully. Cut waffles into quarters, then into quarters again. Cool. Put together with filling.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Season meat with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Heat 1 can enchilada sauce and 1/2 can water to a hot, but not boiling point.
Keep hot while dipping one tortilla at a time until soft.
Remove gently.
Lay flat.
Fill with 2 tablespoons meat, a few chopped onions, grated cheese and 2 tablespoons enchilada sauce.
Roll and place in shallow pan.
When all have been prepared, sprinkle all remaining meat, desired amount of chopped onions and enough grated cheese to cover top. Pour all remaining sauce over the top of the enchiladas.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.
Makes about 12 enchiladas.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, egg, margarine and milk.
Layer in casserole dish with cracker crumbs.
Cook until set, about thirty or forty minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese when done and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: ranch chicken fajita's
directions: Cut chicken into 2 x 14-inch strips.
Brown in skillet.
Stir in pepper strips and cook 1-2 more minutes.
Stir in ranch dressing mix and water.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve in warm tortilla/fajita shells.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix altogether and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pizza grilled cheese
directions: Butter one side of each slice of bread. Place one slice in skillet, butter side down. Top with the cheese, pepperoni, pizza sauce and second bread slice, butter side up. Cook over medium heat until golden brown, turning once. Serve with additional pizza sauce if desired. YIELD: 1 serving.

title: texas roast
directions: Brown onion in oil and add all other ingredients.
Then brown meat.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder together. Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add flour, etc.
Blend well.
Stir in grated zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 pans (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hershey's sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate, butter and boiling water in small bowl; stir until melted.
Thoroughly combine sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, beating until thoroughly combined.
Blend eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed after adding egg mixture to rest of ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Beat eggs first; pour boiling water over oats and let stand. Cream mixtures; add eggs, oats and flour, then mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice omitting salt; set aside. Cook bacon and ham in vegetable oil until bacon is crisp. Add mushrooms and stir-fry over medium heat for 2 minutes. Stir in rice, onions and soy sauce. Stir-fry at medium heat for 3 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: honey lemon chicken breasts
directions: Score chicken breasts diagonally at 1-inch intervals, in diamond pattern, using a sharp knife.
Set aside.
In 9-inch square baking dish, combine remaining ingredients except lemon slices.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add chicken breasts, scored side down.
Coat with honey mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Arrange breast halves scored side up on roasting rack, with meaty portions toward outside.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High for 13 to 15 minutes, or until chicken near bone is no longer pink and juices run clear, rotating rack 2 or 3 times and basting with honey mixture once.
Before serving, garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 4.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except food coloring.
Divide dough in half.
To half of dough, add food coloring.
Blend well. Shape 1 teaspoon of dough from each half into 4-inch rope.
For smooth even ropes, roll them back and forth on lightly floured board.
Place ropes side by side.
Press together lightly and twist.
Complete cookies one at a time.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Curve top of each cookie to form handle of cane.
Bake until set and very lightly browned.

title: cheese straws
directions: Thoroughly blend the butter and cheese.
Sift flour and salt together and gradually add to butter and cheese mixture.
Add red pepper.
Blend well.
Put mixture through cookie press or make into straws and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm, if desired.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and curry powder.
Heat, stirring until well blended.
Combine fruit in shallow 2-quart casserole; add sauce.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: fried rice
directions: In skillet, cook onion in oil until tender.
Beat eggs and add to onion.
Stir until the eggs are cooked thoroughly, but not hard.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Serve as side dish or as a main dish, add 2 cups of diced chicken or ham and 3 cups of any vegetables.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of grated low fat cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat into crock-pot.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Stir to coat meat with flour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours on low or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: pepperoni hot dish
directions: Slice potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger. Put over potatoes.
Heat Cheddar cheese soup and milk.
Pour over hamburger.
Dab with butter and salt.
Stir together tomato soup, 1/2 cup water, oregano and sugar.
Pour over hamburger.
Place slices of pepperoni on top of all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Rebake until cheese melts.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt and mix until smooth, scraping down sides of container if necessary.

title: easy fancy chicken
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Serve over long grain and wild rice.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cool.
Pour over pickles.
Put in refrigerator for 3 days. Take out and put into containers to freeze.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Saut onions in bacon drippings or olive oil. Add okra to onions and garlic. Add vinegar to cut slime on okra. Add tomatoes. add salt, if needed. Cover and cook on low heat until okra is done and ingredients blended.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate chip loaf cake
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Line a loaf pan with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Mix well all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Remove from pan.
Cook completely before slicing.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Put in mixing bowl, add other ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes at 250°.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Fix chocolate cake; cool and cut into chunks.
Make pudding. In large bowl, put 1/2 cake and 1/2 pudding, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1/8-inch thick slices; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add steak, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring almost constantly, until meat is brown. Add green peppers and bouillon; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water; stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until mixture thickens.
Serve with hot Billed rice.
Serves 4.
(Good with egg noodles, too.)

title: lo-cal banana puddin' pie
directions: Layer ingredients in reverse order in pie crust and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and flavoring. Add the milk to the bread and combine with egg mixture.
Drain 1/2 cup juice from pineapple.
Add the remaining juice and pineapple to the mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
(Can be topped with Cool Whip or whipped cream.)

title: baked onion chicken
directions: With rolling pin, crush soup mix in pouch.
On waxed paper, combine soup mix, bread crumbs and pepper.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Mix together and spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter blossom
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape into balls and roll in granulated sugar. Place on ungreased sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Top each cookie immediately with candy kiss.
Cookies will puff up and then will flatten around the kiss.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Cook meat and chopped onions; add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes or until onions are done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel, boil and grate potatoes into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°
in 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: tangy lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika in paper or plastic bag. Brush chicken with lemon juice.
Place a few pieces at a time in bag.
Shake to coat.
Heat oil to 365° in electric skillet or large heavy skillet.
Add chicken.
Brown.
Combine water and bouillon granules.
Stir until dissolved.
Add brown sugar and remaining lemon juice.
Pour into skillet.
Cover.
Reduce heat to 250°; simmer 5 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Sprinkle with onion and lemon peel.
Recover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve garnish with lemon slices and additional parsley.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Blend well together. Stir in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes; cool for 30 minutes.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until covered.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Frost with canned fudge frosting.

title: mixed squash casserole
directions: In a large pot bring water to boil.
Add yellow squash, zucchini, and onions.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 6 minutes. Drain and reserve in a large bowl.
In a small bowl whisk together soup, sour cream, cheese, salt, and pepper.
Add soup mixture to reserved squash.
Mix together.
Transfer to a large baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with crumbled cornbread and with butter.
Bake 10 additional minutes.

title: savory party bread
directions: Cut the bread lengthwise and crosswise without cutting through the bottom crust. Insert cheese between cuts. Combine butter, onion and poppy seeds; drizzle over bread. Wrap in foil; place on a baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Unwrap; bake 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.

title: fruit barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes until slightly thickened.
Baste chicken frequently with sauce.

title: pineapple cake(very moist)
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugar and cream very well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each.
Sift flour and add to preceding mixture alternately with milk that has baking powder dissolved in it.
Beat to mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and stir well.

title: red lobster garlic cheese biscuits(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line baking sheet with wax paper; spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons of the margarine; blend with pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and cheese; combine with fork, handling dough as little as possible.
Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet; bake until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: instant fruit cake
directions: Combine oil and eggs with cake mix.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti rolls
directions: Cook beef in oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until brown, stirring to separate meat; drain fat.
Stir in onion powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in 1 cup of spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Reserve 1/2 cup of ground beef mixture.
Combine remaining beef mixture with cheese in large bowl.
Stuff into manicotti. Arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine remaining spaghetti sauce with reserved beef mixture in small bowl; blend well.
Pour over manicotti.
Cover with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Garnish as desired.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: *The last time, add baking powder.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix in all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, uncovered.
This can be made the day before, refrigerated and then baked.

title: cauliflower with cheese
directions: Cut up in flowerets and boil in salted water 12 to 15 minutes, the cauliflower; drain well and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix salt, pepper, mayonnaise, mustard and cheese.
Spread over cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese, blended with sufficient cream to soften, over bottom of cooled shell.
Place half the berries in cheese-coated shell.
Mash remaining berries (reserving a few for garnish) until juice is well extracted.
Bring to boiling point and slowly stir in sugar and cornstarch which have been mixed together.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool and pour over uncooked berries in shell.
Place pie in refrigerator until very cold.
Decorate with sweetened whipped cream and whole berries just before serving.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: paddy's irish cream
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Shake or blend well before serving over ice.

title: fairy candy
directions: Mix in a large saucepan sugar, vinegar and corn syrup.
Cover lightly and bring to a boil.
Uncover and place a candy thermometer in the pan.
Without stirring, cook over medium heat to 300°.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix together and add enough lukewarm water to make a thick batter.
Let stand in warm place, uncovered, for at least 24 hours or until house is filled with a delectable yeast odor.

title: batter fried zucchini
directions: Put flour in a bowl or plastic bag. In another bowl, put egg and beat with a fork. First, dip zucchini in flour; next, dip in egg, then dip in flour again. Cook in frying pan with 1/2-inch hot oil. Brown one side, then turn over and brown other side. When both sides are browned, they are ready to eat.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
In large casserole dish, mix all other ingredients together; stir well.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover for the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Quickly thaw frozen broccoli by placing in a colander and holding under hot water.
Separate pieces with a fork; drain well. Other ingredients should be at room temperature.
In the order listed, layer ingredients in a large bowl and beat until well blended.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then low 2 to 3 hours.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook onion and hamburger.
Add Chili-O mix and tomato sauce. Cool in refrigerator and dip off grease.
Heat in crock-pot with cheese.
Serve from crock-pot with nacho chips or Doritos chips.

title: 1-2-3 cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form 1-inch balls.
Press down with a fork. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cream of coconut.
Mix well; add extract.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut the lemon in half.
Squeeze all the juice out of each half of the lemon.
Mix with the dressing.
Place dressing mix and chicken together in roasting bag.
Seal.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper with salt and pepper to taste; drain. Pour into casserole dish; add soup, water and rice (uncooked). Mix well and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Greased Bundt pan.
Place biscuit pieces in pan.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: quick peach melba
directions: Place 1 peach half in each of 5 to 6 dessert dishes.
Spoon 1 teaspoon jam over each peach cavity.
Pour milk into small bowl, add pudding mix and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour at once over peaches.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Chill.
Garnish with additional jam, if desired.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and margarine on low heat. Stir until melted. Dip strawberries, one at a time, into the chocolate. Place on wax paper.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour, then add butter, milk, coconut and lemon.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate oatrage snack cake
directions: In large bowl, mix butter, oats, flour, brown sugar, eggs, walnuts and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup chips.
Spread into 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes longer or until top of cake appears dry and bottom is an even color.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top of warm cake.
Let stand 10 minutes, then spread evenly over cake.
Cool directly on countertop.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, cranberry sauce, celery and nuts.
Put in a sprayed 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or mold.
Cover and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli per package instructions, then drain well. Prepare Minute rice per box instructions and drain.
After broccoli and rice have cooled and drained, mix together using all broccoli and all rice.
Stir in jar of Cheez Whiz, cream of chicken soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and put into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour and spread shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Gently stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, combine all wet ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Grease and flour an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan or muffin pan.
Turn batter into loaf pan or fill muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake loaf at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Bake muffins for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy tomato chicken breasts
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Put chicken in baking pan, turning to coat chicken with butter.
Mix onion, tomatoes, paste, basil and garlic.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Mix bread crumbs, parsley, 3 tablespoons butter and cheese.
Pour the cheese mixture over the chicken and bake for an additional 5 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: In large saucepan, melt cheese.
Stir in catsup and spices. Stir in sausage.
Spread a layer completely covering bread onto rye bread and place on cookie sheet.
May be frozen at this point and then stacked in plastic bags for baking.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs; combine with oil, flavorings and strawberries.
Add liquid and dry ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Makes two loaves.

title: sunshine celebration punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine juices; mix well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: green beans and sausage
directions: Cut smoked sausage in to 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute sliced onion with sausage.
Add tomato sauce.
Add 1 can of water or more.
Add basil and garlic powder.
Cut up the peeled potatoes in bite-size pieces and add to sausage.
Simmer until potatoes are about half done.
Add drained green beans.
Stir and simmer, covered.
If it looks dry, add more water.

title: ham casserole
directions: Arrange layers of ham and asparagus in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs, and pour over ham and asparagus.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Over medium heat in a skillet cook rice in oil. When rice starts to brown add chopped onion.
Cook about a minute.
You will smell the onion cooking.
Add tomato sauce, then quickly the water (it will sizzle); stir together.
Slowly add garlic salt to taste.
Put a cover over the skillet.
Reduce heat to low and simmer about 20 minutes.
All liquid should be gone.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine sliced squash and next 4 ingredients; cover with ice. Let stand about 1 1/2 hours.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Heat milk, shortening and sugar to boiling point (do not boil). Set aside until lukewarm. Dissolve 1 package yeast and 1 quart flour in the milk mixture. Set in warm place to rise for about 2 hours. Add second quart of flour and place in the refrigerator or let rise and punch down. Put 3 pinches of dough together in a muffin cup and let rise for 2 hours. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes in gas stove. If electric, bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange bacon over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add pepper, onion, pineapple, seasoning salt and 1 cup of nuts.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in rest of nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Grind and strain the apples, peppers, onions, tomatoes and raisins.
(Use juice for breakfast juice.)
Add seasonings and let stand covered overnight.
Ladle relish into sterilized pint Mason jars to approximately 1-inch from the top.
(Do not overfill.) Seal with hot wax.
When wax is set, cover with 2 piece sterilized Mason lids.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix well eggs, sugar, salad oil and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with Cool Whip or Icing (recipe follows).

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in hot water.
Cool slightly. Stir in strawberries.
Chill until syrupy.
Chill evaporated milk in bowl in freezer until soft ice crystals form.
Whip until stiff.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Beat very stiff.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Add this to the gelatin mixture.
Spoon into 7-cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides; reserve shells.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat potatoes and margarine until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk; stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into reserved shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat into raisin mixture. Stir in nuts.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir only until mixed.	Drop by teaspoon into oil.	Fry 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream and salad dressing mix until well blended.
Add spinach, chestnuts and red pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread(1 pound loaf)
directions: Crush bananas and whip until very light.
Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and beat well. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Add alternately with whipped bananas to egg mixture.

title: venison steaks
directions: My Ma-Ma Fondren said the secret to good venison was to make sure all the "grissle" or the white part on the deer meat was cut off!
(This is what gives it that "gamey" taste.)
Soak the backstrap in the water and baking soda for 1 to 2 hours.
Rinse with clean water.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and cheese well.
Add sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange rind. Mix flour, salt and cinnamon together and then add to creamed mixture.
Load dough into cookie press and create cookies of your choice.
Press on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab-swiss bites
directions: Combine crab, onion, cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Separate each roll into 3 layers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and spoon on crab mixture.
Top each with 2 or 3 slices of water chestnuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in butter in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender; stir in flour.
Add clams, 1/2 tsp. salt, basil and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: raisin frosting
directions: Bake your favorite chocolate cake and frost with this frosting. Grind raisins; add water and sugar and beat.
Cook until thickened. Add margarine.
Ice your cake.

title: *cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a creamy sauce, then add cheese and continue to stir constantly until it melts.

title: garlic pork roast
directions: Make slits all around the roast.
Insert garlic into slits. Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Place in roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes per pound.
Remove from pan and let stand.
Place pan on stovetop over high heat; skim off fat.
Add broth.
Cook until gravy is reduced by half and coat the back of spoon.
Slice meat.
Serve with gravy and horseradish if desired.

title: applesauced potato cakes
directions: Prepare pancake mix according to package directions.
Add luncheon meat.
For each pancake, drop about 2 tablespoons batter on hot, greased griddle.
Bake.
Serve with warm applesauce, dashed with ground cinnamon.
Makes about 10 to 12 small pancakes.

title: kansas cranberry salad
directions: Follow directions on package of gelatin.
Add crushed pineapple and chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce, marshmallows, walnuts and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: emmy's rolls
directions: Sift flour and 1/3 cup of sugar.
Cut in shortening until it resembles cornmeal.
Scald milk and add tap water.	Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add to flour mixture.
Add water and milk (when cool).
Mix well.
Place dough on floured surface and knead.
Place back in bowl and let rise until double in size.
Knead again and refrigerate until ready to use.
Roll out, shape and let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mud balls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and stir until combined.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Dip balls in melted chocolate.
Put on waxed paper in refrigerator to set.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add sausage and Bisquick. Knead by hand.
Shape into small balls and bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: wheat blueberry pancakes
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Stir in eggs, milk, blueberries and butter.
Mix batter until lumps are gone.
Put on griddle 1/4 cup of batter.
Cook until browned on each side. Makes 20 pancakes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, alternating with sour cream and flour.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle half sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with rest of sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until it begins to come away from sides of pan.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add zucchini, flour, soda and baking powder until well mixed.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes 12 servings.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub a 9-inch pie plate with butter. Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake 30 minutes or until set and light golden brown.
Delicious with ice cream.

title: air force chicken
directions: In an electric skillet set on 350°, melt butter.
Lightly brown chicken.
Add all other ingredients over the chicken. Reduce heat to simmer and cook 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Arrange eggs in glass jar; simmer ingredients for 15 minutes. Chill for 24 hours.

title: mustard fried fish
directions: Combine sour cream and mustard.
Dip fillets into the mixture and allow to stand 20 minutes.
Dredge fish in salt and peppered cornmeal and deep fry in oil until browned.

title: mice creams
directions: Put 1 scoop vanilla ice cream into each crust. Tuck cookie ears and tail into ice cream.
Press eyes, nose and whiskers in place.
Makes 6 mice creams.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add the fruit cocktail.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients, except for the brown sugar and the walnuts. The topping is the brown sugar and walnuts.
Put these on top of the cake and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour, add salt and butter in large bowl.
Cut butter in and blend into dry ingredients until you get crumbs.
Add cheese and continue blending until it hangs together and no longer crumbles.
Work 1/4 at a time and roll out in a rectangle 1/3-inch thick and cut into strips (or you can use a pastry press).
Put on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, only until lightly browned.
Cool and store in airtight tins placing wax paper between layers.
Yields about 125 strips.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in plastic milk containers and chill until serving time. Makes 30 (4-ounce) cups.

title: spinach verde
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for approximately 45 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 9 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: very easy german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9x13 pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan. Mix cake and pour on top of nuts and coconut. MIx cream cheese and sugar and oleo. Drop mixture by large spoonfulls on top of cake batter. Bake at 300° one hour and 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove and crumble bacon.
Pour off some of the fat if you wish, for a healthier dish.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Add squash and cook until tender (it does not take long). Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle topping on this and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook meat 2 hours; let cool.
Cut meat fine and return to water.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook at low heat until mixture is thick enough to spread on buns
(3 hours or more).

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients
in
large
mixing bowl.
Add flour and
beat well.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.	Stir in preserves and nuts.
Pour into 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.

title: pickled mushrooms for cocktail party
directions: Brush and clean mushrooms (leave skins on).
Take stems off. Place in saucepan with 2 cups boiling water and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Take out of water.
Cool slightly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into unbaked crust.
Sprinkle with more cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When knife comes clean, it is finished.

title: coconut delight
directions: In oblong baking dish, bake cake mix according to directions using whole eggs and substituting milk instead of water.
When cake is cool, mix 1 can condensed milk with 1/4 cup sugar.
Make holes in cake and pour over cake.
Add layer of drained pineapple, then spread on Cool Whip and top with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: jello dessert
directions: Whip together the Jell-O, cream cheese and leftover pineapple juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Stir ingredients until smooth and add the coconut and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve chilled.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold or an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce.

title: slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil and seasonings; bring to a boil and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Will keep two weeks in refrigerator.

title: wowie cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add liquid ingredients, each in separate corners, pouring water over all. Stir until smooth.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 7-Up. Chill until consistency of heavy syrup.
Mix pineapple, bananas and marshmallows into jello and chill until firm.
Mix sugar and flour into saucepan.
Mix in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Cool.
Stir in cream cheese.
Chill.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle on pecans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, margarine and sugars well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill dough about 30 minutes and then roll well rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Dip each ball top into granulated sugar and flatten slightly on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes in 375° oven until set.
Do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool well before storing.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 things.
Pour this into long casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix corn flakes and butter. Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour pork(without frying)
directions: Add remainder of bouillon.
Salt, pepper and garlic clove.
Mix in until thick.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the artichoke hearts in the bottom of a baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of artichokes.
Season lightly with garlic and pepper. Lay bacon slices on top of chicken and spoon Vermouth over all.
Bake for 40 minutes, draining excess liquid.
Combine the tomatoes and cheese and spoon over the chicken.
Add more garlic, pepper and Vermouth if desired.
Bake for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings. Serve over rice with a green salad.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 2 tablespoons brown sugar, corn syrup, pecans and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Spoon 2 teaspoons of mixture into 9 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Unroll crescent rolls; pinch seams together to form a rectangle.
Mix 1 tablespoon brown sugar with cinnamon.
Spread dough with 1 tablespoon margarine, then sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Roll up from short end.
Cut into 9 slices; place in muffin cups.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Turn out on cookie sheet or tray.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat well.
Place in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: rich crescent rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, salt and eggs with rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Crumble in yeast cakes and stir until dissolved.
Beat in with spoon 4 cups of flour.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl, cover with damp cloth and let rise until double. Shape into rolls, let double and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread mix
directions: Mix nuts and bananas.
Add sugar, egg, milk and biscuit mix to nuts and bananas.
Beat hard for 1 to 2 minutes.
It is very important that you beat this batter well.

title: company chicken
directions: *I precook the bacon strips slightly in the microwave to remove some of the fat.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add Ricotta, Mozzarella, parsley and pepper, then mix by hand until well blended.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in bouillon and water until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.
Partially mash potatoes. Add milk, butter, parsley, cheeses and salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat when it bubbles around the edges.
Do not boil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup with 1 can water.
Stir in next 3 ingredients; put in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chops.
Dredge in seasoned flour and brown in fat.
Place chops in a casserole dish and cover with soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice pepper and onion in small pieces; toss with the carrots. Combine soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and seasoned salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over veggies; seal tightly.
This should be made at least 24 hours before serving.

title: dave's sweet 'n' sour pork
directions: Combine vinegar, juices and tomato paste in a medium pan. Bring to a boil and simmer gently for 10 to 20 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and keep warm.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; blend.
Combine baking powder, soda, flour and salt with grated rind; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
(Grease bottom of glass.)
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp and artichoke orleans
directions: *Change 1/2 pint whipping cream and 1/2 cup milk to 1 cup half and half.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-gallon container.
Add water that is required on the packages for Kool-Aid and for orange juice and lemonade.

title: pot roast milano]
directions: *One cup beef bouillon may be substituted.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave the margarine in a large microwave bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows, toss until coated.
Microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds on High or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately stir in cereal; mix lightly until coated.
Press mixture into pan using greased spatula or waxed paper.

title: avocado salad
directions: Dice up avocado, cucumber, tomato and onion.
Toss together. Add in juice of one lemon and olive oil.
Salt to taste.
Toss together.
Chill until served.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cook pizza dough according to directions on can.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and spices to taste together.
Spread on cooled crust. Layer veggies and top with cheese.
Cut into squares.
Serve cold.
Great appetizer!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Layer
corn
chips,
beef,
green chilies, soup; repeat until all is used.
Pour enchilada sauce over and bake
on low heat
slowly
until
bubbly.
Top
with
Cheddar cheese, or corn chips.
You
may
find
this slightly dry.
In that case, you may add a can of Ro-Tel tomatoes, also Monterey Jack or other cheese may be added.

title: mammy's cake
directions: Mix together, substituting pineapple with syrup for water. Bake according to mix directions.

title: kisses delight
directions: Beat
the egg whites and vinegar together with electric egg beater
in
large
bowl.
Beating around sides of bowl is important
also.
Whites
must
be
stiff and stand in a peak. Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and beat at least 15 seconds.
Then gradually
add
more
sugar, beating well after each addition. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat in.
You may add a drop of red food coloring for pink kisses or 1 tablespoon of fine coconut. Spray 2 cookie
sheets
with
Pam.
Form
into
peaked
kisses pushed from a narrow teaspoon about an inch apart.
Put kisses in preheated oven
at
200° on middle and top shelves and bake for 20 minutes. Then
change
temperature to warm and turn on oven light if you have
one.
Go
to
bed and leave kisses in oven all night.
In the
morning, cut off the oven and light. Kisses should be
crisp, not sticky inside, but if they should be, leave them in oven a little longer to dry.

title: taco pie
directions: Bake pie crust for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 350°. In skillet, cook beef until brown. Drain and add seasoning packet. (I add a little water.)

In separate container, mix beans and 1/3 cup of taco sauce. Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of crust. Add 1/2 of the meat, 1 cup of cheese and chips. Repeat layers excluding chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Add extras such as sour cream, lettuce, tomato and taco sauce. Cut in pie slices and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Add cut pieces of biscuits and shake to coat.
Melt butter in a pan with brown sugar.
Mix well.
Using a tube pan (ungreased), put some of the biscuits into the pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and pour some of the melted butter and brown sugar over the top.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes. Remove bread from pan.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Keeps warm for a while.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread 6 slices of bread with Thousand Island dressing. Top with
cheese, sauerkraut
and
corned
beef.
Cover
with remaining bread.
Brush melted butter
on both sides of bread. Grill on both sides until hot and cheese is melted.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cookies and cream homemade ice cream
directions: Mix egg, sugar, vanilla and Eagle Brand.
Add Oreos.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer and pour milk to fill line.
Makes 4 quarts or 1 gallon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples, sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon in an 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, melted butter, soda and baking powder over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Beat
together	the
cream
cheese,
soups, sour cream, pepper and
onion
and
all seasonings.
Fold into hash brown potatoes. Spoon
into
a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle
with sesame seed and paprika.
Can be frozen at this stage,
but
thaw before
baking.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until bubbly, but not dry.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in heavy boiler and bring to a boil. Turn heat to simmer and let simmer for about 45 minutes or until thick like catsup.
Pour into small bottles and cap.
This is good on meats, but my favorite is fish.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together all liquid ingredients.
Add chiles, onion, cheese, corn meal, corn, baking powder and salt.
Mix and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Start with crackers and make 3 layers of crackers and pudding.
Pour chocolate sauce on top and refrigerate.
Best if refrigerated 4 or 5 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order listed, then muffin mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; use 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Remove from oven and top with about 1 cup cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until golden brown.
It makes 2 large skillets and one small.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole and toss gently with Kitchen Bouquet, coating meat on all sides.
Mix in cream of rice soup.
Cut carrots in quarters lengthwise and in half crosswise.
Add in carrots and remaining ingredients.
Mix gently.

title: beef dip
directions: Chop beef finely.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on Wheat Thins or other favorite crackers.

title: molded mints
directions: Combine shortening, syrup, egg white, 1 pound confectioners sugar, flavoring and food coloring in mixer bowl; beat well.
Beat in as much remaining confectioners sugar as needed to make a stiff consistency.
Shape into balls; roll into sugar.
Press into candy molds.
Let dry for a day.
May be frozen.
Mint mixture can be divided for different flavoring and color.

title: chicken and egg casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces, place in bottom of casserole dish. Chop eggs and sprinkle on top of chicken, add salt and pepper. Mix soups and sour cream together and spread over chicken mixture. Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: louisiana corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix milk, oil, eggs and Tabasco.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add milk mixture.
Stir in corn.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: seoul chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil until moderately hot.
Add chicken and cook until browned, about 10 minutes.
Add garlic and pepper; cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain off excess fat.
In a small bowl, mix together the vinegar, soy sauce, honey and ginger.
Add to chicken.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked.
Serve with rice.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Put 6 tortillas in bottom of casserole. Cover with half of the chicken mixture and the cheese. Alternate again with 6 tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot cider spiced
directions: Heat in coffee pot.
Good for Christmas.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl combine sugar, flour salt and butter.
Add eggs, milk and stir in corn.
Put in a greased casserole and bake uncovered at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: "one pot" dinner(makes a big hit ... especially with the men.)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
If using the 2-quart crock-pot, reduce this recipe by half.

title: bean salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Place lid or cover on bowl.
Yield:
about 7 cups.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill all ingredients; mix in punch bowl.
(Add 7-Up last, just before you serve it.)
Float block of ice or flavored juice on top.
Add orange and lemon slices.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Serves 8 people.

title: grandpa's coffee
directions: Add coffee to water and boil for 2 hours.
Drop in horseshoe; if horseshoe sinks, add coffee and boil longer.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with water to butter mixture.
Blend just until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: amateur lasagna
directions: Thaw the spinach and squeeze dry.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Cut zucchini squash in half lengthwise. Cook the pork sausage, but not overcooked. Hollow zucchini with a melon baller; dice. Mix all ingredients including squash. Stuff the zucchini shells; mound it. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water, cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Congeal until firm.

title: chocolate nut toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat remaining margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and cocoa; mix well.
With floured hands, press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine reserved margarine and sweetened condensed milk; cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over crust.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; immediately top with chips.
Let stand 1 minute; spread while warm.
Top with nuts.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store covered.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned on top or until cheese melts.

title: spinach veggie dip
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.
Serve with any fresh veggies.

title: k.f.c.  cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage and carrots into small pieces about the size of rice kernels. The food processor is great for this. In a salad bowl, combine the sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, vinegar and lemon juice. Beat until smooth. Add cabbage and carrots. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: layered potato salad(this requires an overnight refrigeration)
directions: After boiling, let potatoes cool and cut into thin slices and set aside.
In one bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, celery seed and salt. In another bowl, combine the parsley and onion.
In a large salad bowl, arrange layers in the following order: potatoes, wet mixture and dry mixture.
Continue layering until all potato slices are used.
Do not stir!
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients, drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Cook 7 to 15 minutes, depending on size.

title: margaret's grandma's snickerdoodles(6 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs. Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix and shape dough into balls.

title: empress world tour cuisine german one pot meal
directions: Cut vegetables, apples and meat into bite-sized pieces.
Place steamer in a large pot and add water to just steamer.
Add 1 teaspoon parsley and oregano to water.
Mix remaining spices. Layer meat, vegetables and apples in steamer.
Sprinkle with spice mixture.
Cover pot and bring water to boil.
Heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, whip Milnot.
Add sugar and vanilla.
In small bowl, cream the cream cheese and Jell-O.
Add lemon juice. Combine with Milnot mixture and pour into graham cracker crust, using 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour apples into an ungreased cake pan.
Top with dry cake mix.
Top with slabs of butter.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: amish bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add celery, onion, carrots and parsley.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Saute until soft.
Add bread cubes, turning until all are buttered. Add extra melted butter, if necessary.
Beat 3 eggs until light and pour over mixture.
Stir until all mixture is moistened.
Will fill 10 pound turkey or can be baked in a casserole.

title: pineapple party salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple; add enough water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling point; dissolve lemon and lime gelatin in boiling liquid.
Add salt.
Cool until slightly thickened.
When beginning to congeal, fold in cottage cheese, mayonnaise, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator to chill and set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ultra cocoa mix
directions: Pour the first 3 ingredients into a large, sturdy grocery bag. Seal and shake well. Pour into a 5 pound canister with a tight lid.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples with 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Grease tube pan.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs, orange juice, oil, vanilla extract and baking powder.
Pour 1/2 batter into tube pan.
Add 1/2 apples.
Repeat.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in large kettle.

Pour boiling water over rhubarb. Let stand for about 5 minutes. Drain and squeeze out much of the liquid. Add sugar, egg yolks, flour, butter, water and salt. Cook over low heat until thick. Remove from heat and add the vanilla. pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue. Make meringue with the egg whites. Return to oven and brown.

title: sweet cole slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, cover and place in refrigerator two to four hours.
Combine next 4 ingredients, bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.

title: classic cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cover; chill.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: peachy glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cube up sweet potatoes.
Spray slow cooker with Pam.
Place sweet potatoes in slow cooker and add pie filling and remaining ingredients.
Coat sweet potatoes and cook 2 1/2 - 3 1/2 hours. Just before serving, top potatoes with topping.
Serves 10.

title: mrs. pino's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° on a greased pan.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: In large chilled bowl, whip cream until soft peaks form, add 1/2 c. sugar.
Coarsely crumble gingersnaps and place 1/2 c. in large clear bowl.
Spread 1/3 pumpkin mix over crumbs top with 1/3 cream.
Continue layering ingredients ending with cream.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top for garnish.
May be made two days in advance.

title: asparagus scallop
directions: Mix all ingredients together, folding in asparagus last.
Use 1/4 crumbs for top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: pineapple barbecued beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, garlic and soy sauce.
Put in large greased casserole dish.
Add beans.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Add pineapple plus a portion of the juice until desired consistency.
Mix well.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and press into cheese cake pan.
Bake at 325° until dry, about 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
If desired, add some cinnamon and raisins.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix salt, sugar, syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil in microwave.
Stir.
Boil for 3 minutes in microwave.
Remove and add baking soda.
Mix well and pour over popped corn.
Cook for 30 seconds in microwave.
Remove and mix.
Repeat process 3 more times (4 in all).
Let cool, eat and enjoy.

title: torpedos
directions: Cook onion and hamburg.
Add spaghetti sauce and cook until hot.
Serve in Torpedo rolls with cheese.
Serves 6 to 8 large rolls.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix 2 small boxes apricot Jell-O or 1 family size and crushed pineapple in pan.
Mix all together.
Heat in pan, then cool.
Add Cool Whip, cottage cheese, pecans and buttermilk.
Pour into deep dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt called for. Drain thoroughly. Place broccoli in 10 x 1 1/4-inch baking dish. Combine soup and cheese. Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended. Pour over broccoli in baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are light brown. Serves 6.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Pour off fat. Put sausage, ground beef and remaining ingredients into crock-pot until melted. Serve from crock-pot with tortilla chips.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion, 1 tablespoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper in a large kettle until tender.
Drain.
Put back into kettle and add eggs, butter and milk to desired thickness.
Heat until warm. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: In the bottom of sterilized quart jars, put a large spray of dill, 1 clove garlic and 1 hot pepper.
Pack firm cucumbers, washed and dried, in the jars and fill with brine made of 1 cup salt and 1 cup cider vinegar to each 14 cups of cold water.
Top each jar with another spray of dill and a clove of garlic.
Seal jars and store in a dark, cool spot for 4 to 6 weeks before using.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add table syrup, the beaten eggs, the pecans and sugar.
Beat together well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake slow at 275° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: marge's pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir with a spoon.
Divide in half and roll between waxed paper.
Bake at 425° or according to pie directions.
Makes 2 crusts.
This is an easy pie crust, like playing with play dough!

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Mix 1 cup sifted flour and sour cream together.
Cream sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add to first mixture.
Add the other cup of flour and mix until well blended.
Add baking powder, mixing well.
In a well-greased Bundt pan, place half of batter.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining batter over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter oaties
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine oats, flour and soda. Blend into creamed mixture thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts or coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or just until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove to cooling rack.

title: italian beef
directions: Use crock-pot or 9 x 13-inch baking dish covered with foil. Sprinkle both sides with spices (trim excess fat).
Lay peppers on top.
Pour broth, juices and beer; cover.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
When done, shred meat with fork.
Serve on hard rolls. Crock-pot easiest.
Use 2 roasts and cook all day.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Beat eggs.
Mix sausage, eggs and all other ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and another 15 minutes, uncovered. Bakes best in a glass dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pie filling, pineapple, cake mix and pecans.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend the dry ingredients into the whipped cream and mix well. Add crushed pineapple, along with its juice. Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: oriental shrimp and scallions
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and cook shrimp over high heat, stirring frequently, until shrimp start to turn pink.
Add scallions and continue cooking about 2 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
When cooled, dice fine. Add mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Mix thoroughly, using a silver knife.
Add celery and a sprinkle of salt.
Mix again.
Then add diced eggs with another sprinkle of salt.
Again, mix.
Add Miracle Whip and stir in thoroughly.
If too stiff, add more Miracle Whip.
If too tart, add a little more sugar.
Makes about 1 quart of salad.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add egg and milk; mix together.
Layer in casserole dish:
1st layer, macaroni; 2nd layer, meat mixture and 3rd layer, sprinkle oregano and cover with pizza cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties(yields 6 patties.)
directions: Drain salmon and place in medium mixing bowl.
Add egg and Bay seasoning.
Stir in mustard; add diced onion.
Stir in seafood breader.
Form into patties.
Fry on medium heat until brown.
Then flip; fry until brown.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: Deep fry chicken wings for 15 minutes.
Put them in sauce, then on a tray.
Pour remaining sauce on them and place in a 300° to 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: oven stew(no pot watching)
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and dash of pepper; dredge cubes of beef stew in mixture.
Brown in a little fat.
Place meat in 3 quart casserole.
Add onions, celery, carrots and potatoes. Combine tomato soup, water, 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper, cloves and bay leaf.
Heat.
Pour tomato mixture over vegetables and meat. Cover.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender and potatoes almost tender.
Add the peas or limas.
Cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine next 3 ingredients in bowl; spread over cookie crust and chill 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir.
Return for 5 minutes increments until potatoes are tender.

title: mint julep punch
directions: Squeeze the juice from the lemons.

Add the leaves of the mint, the sugar and water and let stand for 1 hour, then add the ginger ale, the almonds thinly sliced and the cherries cut into 4 pieces; pour this over 8 cups cracked ice and serve.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apple cider or juice, brown sugar and nutmeg.
For spice bag, place cinnamon, allspice and the 1 teaspoon of cloves in cheesecloth and tie; add to cider mixture. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove spice bag and discard.
Serve cider in mugs with a clove-studded orange wedge in each.
Makes 8 (8-ounce) servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding peas last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free hawaiian pineapple pie
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sister's quick 'n easy chicken salad
directions: Break chicken apart with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bread dough
directions: Model into desired shape.
Put in aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven (250° to 350°) for over an hour.
For play only, not edible.

title: florida pie
directions: Blend together milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Drain juice from mandarin oranges.
Beat all ingredients, except pineapple, oranges and nuts.
Slice the bananas and pecans.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans on bottom of oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Top green beans with mixture.
Slice Velveeta cheese thinly on top of sour cream.
Do another layer of sour cream and then another layer of cheese. Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Heat in 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Skewer meat on both sides.
Rub garlic and onion powder on both sides of meat.
Pour the Italian dressing over the meat and marinade for three hours or more; the longer the better.
Put meat on grill for 20 minutes for more or less depending on how you like your meat.
Slice in thin slices.
Good with baked potatoes, salad and garlic toast.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs. May also use potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in frying pan until ground beef is done; drain off excess grease.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick coating.
Heat tortillas for 30 to 45 seconds in microwave.
Put a light layer of enchilada sauce on bottom of pan. Put 1 to 2 spoonfuls of meat mixture onto a tortilla; add Cheddar cheese, then fold the sides up onto the top.
Do the same for each tortilla, placing each into the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining sauce over the tortillas; top with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried pea patties
directions: Pour peas in bowl; mash well with potato masher.
Add egg, salt, pepper, flour and onions.
Mix well.
Pour oil in skillet and cook on medium heat.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown.

title: trey's chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt and pepper; tear into bite size pieces.
Mix tomatoes, soups and 1/3 of cheese together.
Put tortilla shells in bottom of casserole.
Layer chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sesame asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in a skillet; sprinkle with salt if desired. Add 1/2 inch of water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter; add lemon juice and sesame seeds.
Drain asparagus; drizzle with the butter mixture.
Makes 1 serving.

title: choc-nut crisp snack bites
directions: Melt peanut butter, chips and butter in microwave.
Pour over cereal in large bowl (very large).
Mix well.
Empty sugar into brown bag. Shake! Shake! Shake!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Top with half the sausage and 1 cup cheese.
Put remaining bread, then sausage and cheese.
Pour the egg mixture over sausage, bread and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and celery in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add soup and tomato sauce; mix well.
Cook until bubbly.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are light brown at 350°.

title: microwave lasagna rolls(serves 3)
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Drain spinach.
Combine egg, spinach, cottage cheese, half of the Mozzarella cheese, oregano, basil and garlic.
Spread the spinach-cheese mixture evenly on the four lasagna noodles.
Loosely roll each noodle, jelly roll style, starting with short edge.
Place seam-side down in microwave-safe dish.
You can refrigerate at this point until ready to serve. Pour tomato sauce over rolls.
Cook, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes on High in microwave.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: homemade cream soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine chili sauce, horseradish, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl and blend well.
Add celery and Tabasco to taste.
Great with chilled shrimp or with crackers.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: In large pan, cook zucchini, covered in boiling salted water until crisp and tender (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Drain well and set aside.
In same pan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender, not brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mushrooms, dry sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Mix well.
Gently stir in zucchini and Mozzarella cheese.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Thaw berries; dissolve jello in hot water.
Add berries and pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into shallow dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream on top.
Refrigerate until set, then pour remaining mix.
Return to refrigerator.

title: shrimp wontons
directions: *I substitute scallions for regular onions.

title: chocolate cone cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In saucepan, mix butter, water and cocoa powder.
Continually stirring, melt, then remove from heat.
Combine with the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Fill cones to about an inch from the top.
Put ice cream cones into a muffin tin or a big baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Form ball and top with cocktail sauce.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar; set aside.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar, 1 cup warm water, egg, Crisco and salt. Add 1/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Knead and put in large mixing bowl.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Mash down and store in refrigerator, about 2 hours before using.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush rolls with butter.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: elegant fruit cup
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; cool slightly and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add fruits and juices.
Freeze.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, milk and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut dressed and skinned fish into slices about 1-inch thick. Have a deep fat fryer with fat deep enough to completely cover fish, hot and waiting.
Pepper and salt the fish; dip in undiluted evaporated milk. Roll in cracker crumbs or cornmeal and drop into hot fat.
When golden brown, drain and serve hot with lemon juice and hush puppies.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small wedges.
Cook until tender; drain.
In greased casserole dish, place alternate layers of cabbage, soup, milk and cheese mixture.
Top with crumbs and dot generously with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add remaining ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add water and flour.
Add flavoring and pecans.
Roll balls with hands and shape into fingers.
Bake in 350° oven.
While still hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together eggs, Eagle Brand milk, lime juice, salt, food coloring and lime peeling.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3.
Chop fruit cocktail, drain thoroughly.
Mix fruit cocktail and remaining ingredients; beat vigorously 30 strokes. Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf pan.
Remove from pan, cool completely before slicing.
Wrap and remaining tightly in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook zucchini squash in water until tender.
Place 3/4 of stuffing mix on the margarine in the bottom of baking dish.
Add zucchini. Add soup and sour cream (mix together).
Add chopped onion.
Pour on top of zucchini.
Place remainder of stuffing mix on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut each squash in half.
Remove seeds and fibers; peel.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir remaining ingredients (except apples) in a small bowl.
Arrange squash in ungreased baking dish.
Top with apple slices.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven until tender.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix flour and nuts.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until soft peaks form.
Add vanilla and vinegar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg white meringue into chocolate, adding nuts if desired.

title: june punch
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar and 4 cups water 10 minutes.
Add tea and fruit juices.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over a block of ice in a punch bowl or over ice cubes.
Makes 60 to 70 servings.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and baste chicken often while grilling.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter.
Add cheese and blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually to butter cheese mixture.

title: carrot-pineapple bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Drain pineapple; add syrup to dry mixture.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Bake at 325°
for about 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 minutes in pan before unmolding.

title: beef-cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add uncooked rice and set aside.
Mix Italian soup, water and tomato sauce well and set aside.

title: southern fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans.
Line the bottoms with waxed paper.
Set aside.
Combine the pecans, pineapple, peaches, raisins and 1/2 c. flour; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar, add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 1/2 c. peach nectar, honey and milk; beat well (mixture will appear curried).
Combine cinnamon, baking powder, salt, allspice and remaining flour; Add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into prepared pans and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans to a wire rack to cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in a cool place.
Slice and bring to room temperature before serving.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix caramel and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Heat on low until caramels are melted.
In bowl, mix cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Put half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and cook for 6 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and pour chocolate chips over brownie mix.
Then put caramel mix over chocolate chips.
Top with other half of cake mix dough.
Crumble and spread best you can (will not cover completely).
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let set 5 minutes.
Makes 14.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar and oleo in microwave; let cool.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooled milk mixture, egg and salt.
Stir in 4 cups flour and no more.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out cold dough on lightly floured board.
Spread with one stick melted oleo.
Sprinkle with 2 cups brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut rolls and put in pan.
Let rise and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar, vanilla and boiling water.
Drizzle over rolls.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt, and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk and add melted Crisco and whole kernel corn.
Combine two mixtures lightly.
Drop from a tablespoon into shallow Crisco heated to 365°.
Fry until brown and cooked in center, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with maple syrup.
Makes 15 to 20 fritters.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, salt.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick; remove, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pastry and top with meringue (egg whites beaten until stiff, gradually adding 6 tbsp. sugar; continue to beat until stiff and glossy).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, on medium heat to a boil.
Boil and stir five minutes.
Stir in until melted, 6 ounce package of chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir in 1 cup of nuts.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
When this mixture is lukewarm, add warm water and yeast.
Stir in white flour.
When dough is stiff enough to handle, turn onto floured board and knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack, brushing loaves with margarine for a soft crust.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Lightly brown finely chopped onion in oil in saucepan.
Mix in chili powder, water and hamburg.
Bring to boil; add salt, pepper, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: betty-gine's apple crisp
directions: Put apples in shallow 2 quart casserole and add water.
Combine sugars, spices, salt and flour in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender, until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon evenly over apples.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
