Serve hot or cold with sweet cream or ice cream. Good plain too.

title: glorified rice dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Measure syrup and add water to measure 1 1/4 cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cherries and pineapple.
Chill thoroughly.
Fold marshmallows and Cool Whip into chilled rice mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, cool, peel and slice.
Cook bacon until crisp, drain and reserve 2 Tbsp. drippings.
Add onion to drippings and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed, and pepper.
Add water and vinegar, stir and cook until thickened.
Add potatoes and bacon.
Cook until heated through.

title: raisin bread
directions: Cook raisins in water slowly for 20 minutes.
Cool, drain and save liquid.
Cream sugar, egg and shortening.
Add enough water to liquid to make 3/4 cup in all.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with liquid.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Fill buttered round bean cans or tomato cans 1/2 full and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes for bean can/1 hour for tomato cans.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: First, you make a roux:
in a large saucepan, melt butter. Then, add flour.
Brown mixture by stirring continuously over medium high heat.
(Approx 10 minutes - the key to not burning this mixture is to keep stirring).
Stir in chopped roasted garlic. Then add celery, parsley, bell peppers and red onion.
Stir until the celery and onion are clear.
Continue stirring.
Add red wine. Boil off the alcohol.
Add the can of tomatoes and 2 cups of water. Add Tony's seasoning - amount depends on personal preference. Cook, stirring occasionally until mixture begins to thicken.
This should take approx 45 min.
Add drained crawfish tails.
Continue cooking for approx 15 min.
When almost finished, add the chopped green onions.
Etouffee should always be served over prepared rice. The rice and etouffee should not be mixed in one pot.
Add tabasco sauce if desired.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: walnut rum balls
directions: Mix ingredients well; add syrup and rum.
Roll into 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: broiled tuna sandwiches
directions: Spread buns with butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread on buns.
Broil sandwiches, open-faced, until hot and golden brown (about 5 minutes).

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Bake in tube angel food pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Turn off oven and leave cake in oven for 15 minutes more.
Grease and flour pans.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices crosswise but not all the way through.
Use a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a micro-safe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes at High power until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve potatoes as a side dish or as a main dish with just a salad.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix meat, soup mix and cheese and flatten on bottom of pan. Mix mushroom soup and milk together.
Line up Tater Tots on hamburger mixture and pour mushroom soup and milk over it.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Combine the beans, picante sauce, rice, beef and half of the cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes, until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients slowly until sugar is dissolved. Slow-boil for 12 minutes or until thick.
Add jello in mixture; stir.
Take off heat.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken elegant
directions: Cover chicken breasts with Swiss cheese.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Add 1 stick butter (1/2 cup) with 2 cups herb stuffing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
You may use Stove Top dressing.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 cup. Mix sugar and flour together in saucepan and beat in egg; add water and juice gradually.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and mixture boils.
Cool.
Stir in chunks of pineapple.
Garnish top with marshmallows and nuts.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar,
flour, salt; add slightly beaten egg yolks, water and butter.
Cook
until thick.
Pour in baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Makes 1 pie.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and flour.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Swirl into previous mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Looks like an earthquake, but is heavenly.

title: oriental meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, dry mustard, salt, pepper, egg and milk.
Shape into meat balls.
Brown meat balls in fat.
Pour off dripping.
Drain pineapple, reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Mix together sugar, ginger, salt and cornstarch; add 1/2 cup pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened; add to brown meat balls.
Cook about 5 minutes, add tomato wedges, green pepper strips and pineapple chunks.
Cook until heated.
Serves 6.
Can be served on rice.

title: swiss steaks
directions: Cook onions down first, then add the mushroom soup.
This is to make the gravy.
Add chicken seasoning and vegex; mix well and put in the oven for at least 30 minutes.
If you have soy sauce add 1 teaspoon to the mixture.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and frost.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and add 2 cups of the sugar gradually, beating until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, very well.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in flour, sifted with the baking powder and salt. Combine remaining sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Place about 1/3 of the batter in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 3/4 of the pecan mixture.
Spoon in remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans and bake about 60 minutes or until done. Cool on a rack.
If desired, glaze with a mixture of 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, 2 teaspoons hot milk and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Let chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (like pie crust).
Press 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel and core apples. Add apples to the pan until 3/4 full.
Cover with other 1/2 of crumbs. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour, until fork-tender, at 350°.

title: fruity pudding salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix with undrained pineapple in a bowl; mix well.
Add oranges, whipped topping, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until tender.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Simmer 30 minutes or until thickened.
Pour into hot pint jars and seal.
Yields 9 pints.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oil in skillet (8 to 10-inch).
Beat eggs with water, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour into skillet and reduce heat.
Let eggs cook until bottom is firm.
Lift edges and let uncooked egg go underneath.
Cook until top is nearly firm.
Spoon tomato sauce over egg.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese and cook under broiler until bubbly and melted.
Serve in wedges, just like pizza!

title: savory hamburger supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in 3-quart saucepan; drain.
Add chili powder and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni, tomatoes and corn.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese packet.

title: apple brownies
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fish au gratin
directions: Layer fish and cheese in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices.
Cook onion in hot oil in skillet until tender, but not brown.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly for 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water 3 minutes. Drain.
Pour milk into small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook to lukewarm.
Mix eggs with salt and nutmeg. Add milk and cheese, beating constantly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Add broccoli. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Serve hot.

title: holly cookies
directions: Heat margarine and marshmallows in a double boiler until melted.
Add vanilla and green food coloring (until desired green color is reached).
Pour over corn flakes and stir until flakes are green.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper and place red candies in center at once.

title: dump cake
directions: In large mixing bowl dump all of the ingredients.
Stir gently.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: toasted coconut pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cut beef or chicken into strips. Season with 2 tablespoons soya sauce and cornstarch.
Heat wok and add 2 tablespoons of oil; when hot add garlic and onion until brown.
Add meat and stir-fry until done.
Add vegetables for 2 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of soya sauce and oyster sauce.
Add noodles.
Stir-fry until well mixed.
Add salt for taste.

title: rice creole dish
directions: Saute onions in olive oil until golden brown. Add bell pepper and celery. Saute briefly. Add tomatoes. Cover; simmer until tomatoes become liquified. Add rice, lemon juice, basil and seasonings. Bring to a boil; lower heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Add cheese on top. Melt cheese under broiler or replace lid and let cheese melt through.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoonful vanilla and salt. Blend at medium speed.
Pour into shell and sprinkle with pecans on top.
Combine 3 eggs, corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoonful vanilla.
Blend at medium speed, pour this mixture over top of pecans.
Bake at
375° for 35-40 minutes.

title: spam salad
directions: Use as spread on crackers or sandwich.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in water.
Reserve soaking liquid.
Sliver mushrooms, pork and bean curd.
Mince scallion.
Beat egg lightly. Blend cornstarch and cold water to make a paste.
Bring stock and mushroom-soaking liquid to a boil.
Add pork and mushrooms and simmer covered 10 minutes.
Add bean curd and simmer, covered, 3 minutes more.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: In saucepan, mix first 7 ingredients. Heat until combined. Pour this mixture in unbaked shell. Beat eggs and milk together. Pour over first mixture. Use lattice crust for top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cover edge with foil and bake another 10 to 15 minutes until knife comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: peppers and cheese
directions: Mash crackers and mix the cheese and peppers together. Prepare peppers to stuff with mixture. The more veins removed from the peppers, the cooler they will be. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: hasty chicken and dumplings(good for leftover chicken)
directions: If you think it is too thick, add 1 can chicken broth.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, sour cream, eggs, water and oil.
Blend well.
Add chocolate chips, German chocolate (melted) and nuts (if desired).
Bake in tube pan for 55 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Shell, devein and wash shrimp.
Cut in chunks.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Lightly grease bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle peppers and cheese in the bottom of the pan.
Combine Bisquick, beaten eggs, cream and salt.
Beat until thoroughly blended. Pour over peppers and cheese.
Top with chopped olives.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 375° or until puffed and golden.
Best served warm.

title: tator candy
directions: Peel and boil potato.
When done, mash up with fork; add a pinch of salt and pour in powdered sugar.
This makes a very stiff dough.
Roll on dough board that has been floured real good.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread a thin layer of peanut butter all over top and roll up like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Batter in flour; put in pan with oil and lightly brown.
Put in colander and drain.
Cover meat with water.
Add carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook in crock-pot until done.

title: cheese log
directions: You will need wax paper and aluminum foil.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan. Spread cherry pie filling over top of pineapple evenly, but do not mix.
Spread the dry cake mix over top and then sprinkle the nuts on top of this.
Slice the margarine and place over top of nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake begins to brown.
Do not let the nut meats burn.

title: taco salad
directions: Have on hand all of the items.
Cook chili (your recipe) and rice according to directions.
Chop all vegetables and nuts to your liking.
Prepare enough of each item according to the number of people you are going to serve.
Have guests start creating their salads, beginning with the first item on the list.
This salad grows, so be careful.
Mix up carefully (ha!) and eat. Delicious!

title: coney sauce
directions: Do not brown ground chuck.
Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 hours on medium heat.

title: swedish glogg
directions: Remove seed from cardamom pods (should have 20 to 25 seed); tie with cinnamon, cloves and orange peel in cheesecloth bag.
In large saucepan, combine half the Port, half the Burgundy and the raisins; add the cheesecloth bag.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add the remaining wine and the almonds; heat through. Place sugar in another saucepan.
Warm about a third of the brandy; pour over sugar and light with a match to flame.
When sugar has melted, extinguish flame by pouring in the remaining brandy.
Add sugar mixture to wine mixture.
Serve warm.
Float halved orange slices studded with whole cloves in each cup, if desired.
Yield:
20 (8 ounce) cups.

title: turkey and broccoli bake
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and pepper. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Layer broccoli, turkey and sauce in a 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green and gold mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Add carrots and cheese.
Pour into a ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; fill center with sour cream or salad dressing.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: egg in a frame("kid's cooking")
directions: Cut a hole in the center of the bread with an upside-down drinking glass.
Melt one pat of margarine in a small frying pan over low heat.
Toss in the bread and break the egg into the hole. Don't worry if you break the yolk.
Cook until the bread is golden brown on the bottom.
Turn the bread (with egg) over, put the remaining margarine in the pan and use your spatula to make sure it gets under the toast.
Fry until egg looks done.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and spice in a large kettle. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add a dozen peaches at a time and cook slowly until tender.
Remove and pack in sterilized jars.
Continue to cook peaches 12 at a time until all are cooked and packed in jars.
Boil the remaining syrup over moderate heat for about 15 minutes or until thick as desired.
Pour over peaches in jars and seal.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Stir in salt, melted butter and Karo. Add pecans, last.
Bake in pie shell for 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until brown, or until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean, approximately 25 minutes.

title: chunky apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drain apple chunks.
Mix yogurt and eggs in a large mixing bowl; beat to combine.
Add dry muffin mix; stir in with fork.
Fold in apple chunks.
Do not beat.
Pour all but 1 cup of batter in greased pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken.
Take off bone.
Put chicken, plus 2 cans soup, back in broth.
Heat.
Add margarine.
Stir until margarine is melted; pour into pan.
Mix 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and flour. Add 1 cup milk.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: pretzels
directions: Thaw dough.
Roll small amount into snake shape.
Twist.
Melt butter; brush on dough.
Salt lightly.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned on top.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix well until flour disappears.
Roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Mash down slightly on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Pour off excess fat, leaving 1/2 cup in skillet. Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper and blend well.
Add vinegar and water. Cook until thick and pour over potatoes.

title: dilly pumpernickel dip
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Hollow out center of loaf and put dip into hole.
Cut or break leftover bread into bite sized pieces.
Use additional loaves to make more dippers.

title: popovers
directions: Generously grease six 6-oz. custard cups or 8 muffin cups. Set aside.

In a large mixing bowl beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients and beat on low speed of electric mixer until smooth. Fill cups about 3/4 full with batter. Bake in preheated, 400° convection oven on rack 2, 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes longer (or bake in preheated 425° radiant bake oven 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer) or until deep golden brown. Remove from pan. Serve warm. Yield:
6 to 8 popovers.

title: clam, bacon and onion canapes
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the clams, the bacon, the onion, the parsley, the Parmesan cheese and the mayonnaise until the mixture is combined well.
Spread 1 teaspoon of the mixture on each toast round, mounding it.
Broil the canapes in a jelly-roll pan under a preheated broiler about 4-inches from the heat for 3 to 4 minutes, or until they are bubbly and golden.
Makes 18 canapes.

title: doves sauteed with bacon cream sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute the bacon until just crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: marty's mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and spread on tortillas. (Spread like butter on bread.)
Roll tortillas end to end and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
(Can be frozen.)
Remove wrap and slice in 1-inch slices.
Spear with toothpicks.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: toffee bars
directions: Pat in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Melt chocolate chips over top.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix lime jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Allow to cool until lukewarm.
In a blender combine jello mixture with the softened cream cheese and heavy cream.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into jello mold and refrigerate until set.
Unmold and serve.

title: pineapple-rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in about 1-quart salted water until soft (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Strain in colander and cool off with cold water. Place rice in mixing bowl and add sugar, egg yolks, salt, butter, vanilla, milk and crushed pineapple.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten stiffly.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: date nut puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat until egg whites hold peaks.
Add brown sugar, a few tablespoons at a time and continue beating until mixture forms glossy, pointed peaks.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto unglazed brown paper on cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from paper to wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: If using canned fruit, be sure it is well drained.
Be sure fruit is cut into medium size pieces.
Set aside.
In medium size boiler, mix sugar and cornstarch, add Sprite.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and turns clear, remove from heat.
Add box of Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Pour over fruit stirring carefully until all fruit is covered.
Chill and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Then add milk, bananas, flour and pecans.
Mix well.	Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Tear up cake into ice cube sized chunks.
Use 1/2 of each and layer: cake, pudding, fruit and Cool Whip.
Use other half and layer again.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours; best if overnight.

title: taco party wings
directions: Shake taco seasoning, cornmeal, salt and parsley flakes in a bag.
Shake a few wings at a time.
Place in a single layer on greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes. Turn wings and bake 10 minutes or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: pear honey
directions: Puree the pears in a food processor or blender; pour into a large kettle or Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cook and stir, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 20 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yield: 12 half pints.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well. Store in airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water or use 2 to 3 teaspoons per glass of cold water and ice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Make three depressions in mixture.
Add oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in one.
Pour water over all.
Mix gently with fork. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado in medium size bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Spread avocado mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 inch flat-bottomed dish. Mix bean dip and taco seasoning; layer over avocado. Layer onions, tomatoes, and olives above bean dip. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Layer above vegetables, top with cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: souper special
directions: Mix soup, milk, eggs and pimento.
Heat through in a saucepan, stirring gently.
In another saucepan, heat asparagus.
Toast bread; cut diagonally.
Place toast on plate, top with asparagus and pour on sauce.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Can be rolled into a ball or served from a bowl.
Tastes best with toasted wheat or cheese crackers.

title: chicken salad with grapes and toasted almonds
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, grapes and celery.
In a small bowl, blend sour cream, mayonnaise and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Mix with chicken mixture and chill.
Just before serving, stir in almonds.

title: creamy chicken manicotti
directions: Cook shells according to package directions, omitting salt; drain and put on wax paper.
Combine soup, green chilies and sour cream; mix well.
Combine half of soup mixture and chicken.
Mix well.
Reserve remaining soup mixture; set aside.
Stuff manicotti shells with chicken mixture.
Place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender; set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt and bananas.
Add flour and soda, sifted together.
Use nuts, if desired.
Bake in loaf pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 320°.

title: crab cheese spread
directions: Beat together cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder. Blend in chicken, celery, onion, garlic salt and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Shape into log and lay on Saran Wrap, cover with remaining parsley and almonds.
Chill.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: brunch surprise
directions: For each sandwich you will need the above ingredients.
First, you toast a piece of bread lightly.
Set aside.
On this, put a slice of hot ham and then top with a double slice of Swiss cheese. Insert under the broiler until cheese has melted.
Meanwhile, poach an egg and place on top of toast, ham and cheese combination.
Now, add a dash of Tabasco sauce.

title: grandma dellar's dill pickles
directions: You will need canning jars, lids and rings for this recipe.

title: pickled okra
directions: Scrub tiny okra pods with vegetable brush.
To prevent floating of product, place about a quart of okra in a perforated blanching basket.
Lower okra into 3 or 4 quarts boiling water.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Chill in cold water.

Place pods upright into pint or half-pint standard canning jars alternating big and little ends. To each pint, add 1 teaspoon dill seed or a small sprig of dill, 2 cloves garlic, and a tiny pod of hot pepper.

title: basic pizza sauce
directions: Lightly coat large nonstick skillet with olive oil.
Heat over medium.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes with juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 30 minutes.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Use sauce immediately or cool and refrigerate, covered, for up to 4 days or freeze for up to 1 month.

title: my favorite hot and spicy pickles
directions: Slice pickles in rounds.
Layer pickles, sugar, hot sauce and garlic in the gallon pickle jar.
Refrigerate 5 to 7 days, stirring periodically to dissolve sugar.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 12 1/2 pints.

title: pineapple loaf bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, until top is brown and toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: swiss bacon pleasers
directions: Into the bottom of a greased and well floured pan, spread rolls flat and 1 inch up the sides.
Use two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Mix all other ingredients together; pour over the flattened rolls.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares and serve.

title: broccoli salmon bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt margarine.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and stir until thick and smooth.
Add salt, dill weed and pepper.

title: mint dessert
directions: Whip the cream until stiff.
Add cut-up marshmallows and crushed candy.
Add nuts.
Put in a cake pan and cover with crushed wafers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good for Christmas. Serves 12.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Saute onions in oleo until tender.
Add cheese to hot mashed potatoes; mix.
Place 3 noodles in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put 1/2 of potato mixture over noodles and 1/3 of the onion mixture and spread evenly. Place 3 more noodles and the rest of the potato mixture.
Add remaining noodles and onion mix.
Cover well with onion mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with lettuce.
Then continue layering with the peas, onions, peppers, celery, mayonnaise and cheese on top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then serve.

title: blueberry pineapple dessert
directions: Spray large dish with Pam spray. Place large can pineapple on bottom. Layer blueberries on top of pineapple. Add crumbled cake mix on top. Pat with butter and sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello, using only 1 1/2 cups liquid per box.
This includes the drained fruit juice.
Grind cranberries, oranges, etc.
Mix together and chill.

title: strawberries & cream
directions: Mix condensed milk with ice water, add pudding, mix well and chill.
While pudding chills dice pound cake.
Combine cool whip with chilled pudding.
Layer in large bowl.
Begin with cake and cover with thawed strawberries.
Cover berries with pudding and ending layering with pudding.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: gator tail 'n taters
directions: Boil gator tail in large pot with black pepper, salt and red pepper until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Arrange potatoes around; dot with butter and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into round pieces.
Put in casserole dish mixed with sliced onions.
Add soup and milk with salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Top with pieces of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: twinkie cake
directions: In double boiler, cook 1 cup milk with 5 tablespoons flour. Stir constantly, until mixture becomes thick.
Remove from heat. While hot, add to sugar mixture and mix until fluffy.
If frosting is not thick enough, add more butter and Crisco.
Remove cake from cake pan.
Cut in half.
Put 1 half back in pan and frost.
Put second half on top of first half and frost top.

title: oreo and ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine and add to cookies.
Spread ice cream over cookies.
Put fudge over ice cream.
Add whipped cream on top of that.
Decorate with nuts or crushed cookies.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.

title: prune cake with butterscotch glaze
directions: Mix well eggs, oil, sugar and spices.
Fold in flour and buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° in preheated oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in tube pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add at once all remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Drop onto wax paper. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and arrange in greased baking dish. Place chicken pulled apart on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Top with crescent rolls.
Bake at 350°
until golden brown.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet; add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes; covered.
Add onion mixture to beans and add crumbled bacon.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and onion.
Pour the cup of sugar over this and let stand.
Combine remainder of ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.

title: family taco casserole
directions: Crush tortilla chips to coarse crumbs.
Set aside.
Crumble ground beef into medium-size glass bowl.
Add onion.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasoning mix.
Microwave on High until boiling (about 3 minutes).

title: bourbon slushies
directions: In a large container, put frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade, sugar and tea bags.
Pour boiling water over this mixture and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove tea bags.
Add bourbon and cold water.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Put container in freezer.
(Mixture wil not freeze solidly due to the alcohol.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot (not boiling) water until melted.
Gradually stir in sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, stirring well after each addition. Mixture will be very thick and dry.
Add salt and milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 cups.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have oleo, butter and cream cheese at room temperature.
Cream all three together until creamy.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add flavorings.
Beat again.
Use 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: bow ties and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, black olives and garlic.
Saute for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cook bow tie pasta.
Combine with sauce and add Romano cheese.

title: peanut crunch cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cake mix, peanut butter and brown sugar on low speed until crumbly. Set aside 1/2 c. crumbs.

title: ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of hot sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 package of dry dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with celery sticks and other Ranch dressing mix, prepared as a dip.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook macaroni; brown ground beef and combine both with spaghetti sauce.
Put 1/2 into large baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 pint cottage cheese.
Cover with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Prepare cake following directions on cake mix.
Mix the cinnamon and sugar together.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a tube pan and sprinkle half the cinnamon/sugar mixture and half the walnuts.
Mix with a knife without touching bottom of pan.
Pour the remaining batter in and add the rest of the cinnamon/sugar mixture and walnuts.
Mix with a knife.
Bake according to the directions on the box.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour half the batter over prepared crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife whirl through batter to marbleize.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Store in icebox.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into greased oblong baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes longer, or until nuts are lightly toasted.

title: hamburger steak sauce
directions: Melt butter and saute onion, celery and parsley until limp. Add mushrooms and cook for about 7 minutes.
Add salt, basil, pepper and flour.
Add water and lemon juice; cook slowly for 5 minutes until thick and bubbly.

title: baked tenderloin
directions: Salt, pepper and flour tenderloin.
Fry in 2 tablespoons oil until golden brown.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Mix soup and mushrooms.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cape codder
directions: Mix and pour into a tall glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Spread melted butter over crust.
Spread crumbled cooked bacon or crumbled cooked sausage over the bottom of crust.
Spread grated cheese over this.
Combine remaining ingredients. Beat with mixer. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for approximately 50 minutes more or until set.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix together the milk and eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour milk mixture into flour; mix thoroughly.
Test mixture to see if it flows easily through funnel.
If too thick, add milk until consistency is right.
If too thin, add more flour.
Heat deep fat in heavy iron skillet or pan.
Pour batter through funnel into deep fat.
Spiral and other shaped cakes can be made by manipulation of funnel and control of outlet finger.
Fry; drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.
Serve hot.
Good with ice cream or with sausage and syrup.

title: seafarer's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease casserole for ease in cleaning. Mix soup and vegetables and put in casserole dish.
Mix mashed potatoes per directions on package, adding the Parmesan cheese. Spoon mashed potatoes on top of vegetables and soup; top with French fried onions, a few dashes of paprika.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Can be frozen before baking for later use.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together and pour over balls.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered in a deep pan.

title: fresh peas with new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and peas in separate pans of salted water until soft and almost free of water.
Put peas and potatoes together in pan, add milk.
Bring to a boil, add the
butter and flour which have been blended until smooth, cook until thickened.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour; beat well after each cup.
Blend in lemon and 7-Up.
Pour into prepared 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: First brown hamburger meat in skillet, adding onion, pepper and salt. After browning, drain grease. Let cool for about ten minutes.
Then in a bowl, mix Jiffy corn bread mix, adding milk, creamed corn and pimento.

Stir in all ingredients. Then take a 5 x 12 baking pan; sprinkle ground meat at the bottom, then pour corn bread mix on top. Then lay slices of Velveeta cheese on top. Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Cook until brown. After baking, let the dish cool for 30 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.

title: beef and rice hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add dehydrated onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper.
Stir, then add the rice and seasoning packets you'll find in the rice. Add water, according to directions on the box. Cover.
Let simmer until all water is absorbed.
Stir well, then serve.
Serves 8.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Peel peaches and cut into small pieces.
Cut and seed oranges and lemon (do not peel).
Process, peel and all, into fine pieces.

title: shrimp log
directions: In bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in shrimp, chili sauce, olives, onion and lemon juice.
Shape into a log and garnish with sliced stuffed olives.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm hearty wheat crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: crowd pleasing vegetables
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli according to package directions. Cut up any large pieces.
Combine two styles of corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.
Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: no-lemon flat cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine and 1 beaten egg.
Press in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chicken sauce picante
directions: Cut up chicken.
Cook all vegetables in oil until tender.
Put all in a heavy pot.
Add water and chicken.
When chicken is done, add 1/2 of lemon.
Mix cornstarch in a cup with water.
Pour in pot; cook until thick.
May have to add water along when needed. Serve over rice.
You may want to debone chicken.
This is usually hot with pepper.

title: pear-lime gelatin salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving juice.
Set pears aside.
Measure the juice; add water if needed to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Pour into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Gradually add cream cheese, whisking until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate until cool.
Mash reserved pears; fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a 6-cup serving bowl.
Refrigerate until set.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; drain.
Peel and mash thoroughly. Add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine whipping cream and cheese; spread over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
This may be prepared ahead of time and browned just before serving.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Will make about 8 1/2 dozen.

title: gulliver's cream corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except for flour and butter and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend together butter and flour and add to corn; mix well.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: date chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together dates, boiling water, and 1 tsp. baking soda. Let cool.
Add Crisco, eggs and vanilla to cooled date mixture. Stir in remaining dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan. Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top each piece with Cool Whip before serving.

title: orange poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all together for 2 minutes, then pour into lightly greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots 6 to 8 minutes, until just tender, not soft. Drain and cool quickly.
Mix vegetables.
Mix all other ingredients well, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate overnight or 10 hours before serving.
This will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.
You might like more salt and pepper.

title: my mother's "best" salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together except cornstarch and water.
Boil until clear and add to other ingredients.
Stir until mixed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, salt, vanilla, lemon and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda; add flour mixture alternately to the sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.
Top while hot with Brown Sugar Glaze.

title: roasted winter vegetables(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Put butter, tarragon, salt and pepper in a shallow roasting pan.
Put pan in oven just long enough to melt butter.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Cut onions into wedges.
Toss onions in butter mixture and roast uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cauliflower.
Continue roasting until vegetables are tender, about 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown and cook hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet. Drain; add pork and beans and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: b.b.q. beans
directions: Place Pork-N-Beans in a pot.
Cook bacon, place in pot.
In bacon grease, saute bell pepper and onions, then add all the above to beans.
Add yellow mustard and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Simmer for 5 minutes more, then serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in strips and brown.
Add onions, mushrooms and salt or garlic juice.
Mix tomato soup with juice from mushrooms, the sour cream and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over meat; cook until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Soak crackers in milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into oblong patties and brown very slowly in skillet.
After browning both sides, place in a baking dish.
Make brown gravy from pan drippings and pour over steaks.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding mix until pudding is dissolved. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts, marshmallows and coconut.
Chill.

title: my best cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix walnut pieces and cinnamon and grind. Butter a cake pan.
Place 1 sheet of phyllo in pan and butter.
Repeat for 10 sheets of phyllo.
Then sprinkle with walnut mixture, add a sheet of phyllo, butter, waluts, phyllo, butter, etc. until pan is almost full.
Cut almost through to bottom of pan in diagonal pattern; place in oven for about 1 hour, until top is browned.

title: baked chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange chicken in single layer with skin down in melted butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes longer, until tender.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat. Combine evaporated milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
(Add more evaporated milk for thinner gravy.)
Add onion and mushrooms to chicken. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover dish with foil.
Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.
(Gravy is delicious over rice or egg noodles.)

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch heavy cast-aluminum Bundt pan.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream oil and sugar until well mixed.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Beat in hot water.
Sift rest of dry ingredients.
Beat into egg mixture.
Stir in 1 1/2 cup carrots, then pecans.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into batter.
Put into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar; blend good.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat until all eggs are added.
Add flour and 1/2 cup milk; beat, then add the remaining milk.
Blend the mixture good, then add the flavorings and blend.

title: strawberry cheese(serves 2)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken; set aside.
Saute onion in butter in large saucepan; add soups and tomatoes.
Crush chips and place in bottom of 13-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over chips.
Layer 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of soup mixture; repeat, ending with soup mixture.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix together in a blender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash 10 minutes.
Saute onion until brown in 1/2 stick of butter.
Add eggs, crumbs, cheese and soup together.
Add squash and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mary's fluffy rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add boiling water.
Let cool and then add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, then add to mixture.
Work in salt and flour. Cover and put in warm place for 2 hours to rise.
Then work down and roll out. Cut like biscuits.
Place in lightly greased pan and let rise 1 hour. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; press into a 9 x 9 baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Combine pudding and milk; pour and spread on top of filling.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: old fashion mac and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: oven stew
directions: Bake, covered, at 225° for 4 hours.

title: roasted winter vegetables
directions: Place butter and spices into shallow roasting pan in oven just to melt butter. Cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Cut onions into wedges. Toss onions in butter, mix and roast, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir in remaining veggies. Continue roasting until tender.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.
Other combinations of vegetables are quite yummy.

title: grandma charron's rice and artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice and add onions, pepper, celery, artichokes, olives, curry and mayonnaise. Blend well. Add pecans last.
Serve warm temperature or cooled.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend together salt, pepper, milk and soup.
Layer potatoes and onions in a greased 11 x 7-inch dish.
Pour soup mixture evenly over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until soft.
I cover for 1/2 hour to cook potatoes and then uncover for the remainder of time.

title: egg, cheese, potato casserole
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes until done.
Peel the skin off of the potatoes.
Take the shells off the eggs.
Slice eggs and potatoes. Make a layer of potatoes, then a layer of eggs, then a layer of cheese.
Keep doing this until the casserole dish is full.
Pour white sauce made of butter, flour and milk over dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli cornbread(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam. Mix all ingredients in order given until well blended.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
This makes a large amount of bread.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Leftovers are good toasted. Serves 8.

title: chocolate cake(no eggs)
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Make 3 holes in the above; add shortening, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour water overall.
Mix together and put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad(club member: terah smith)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add tomato paste and seasoning mix.
Put Frito chips in bottom of cooking pan.
Add mixture on top of chips and top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Use lettuce and tomato as you desire.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all in one bowl.
Start with cake mix and end with pecans. Be sure to blend after each addition.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Pour 1/2 batter in pan, sprinkle 1/2 of brown sugar and cinnamon over it.
Pour rest of batter then sprinkle with the rest of brown sugar and cinnamon.
When done and still hot, mix 1 cup of powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Spread on top while cake is still hot.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix together the buttermilk, melted butter or margarine and egg.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ingredients.
Carefully stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 8 large greased cups or 12 smaller ones. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans.
Serve hot.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine ingredients and add enough olive oil to make a paste. Spread over meat.
Put into a crock-pot on low setting and cook all day.
Use as a meal with pasta or it makes great sandwiches.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; add soup, sauce and water.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with meat mixture, then tortillas and cheese.
Layer top with meat and cheese.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes until bubbly and top is brown.
Servings:
about 6.

title: chicken stir-fry(curry)
directions: In large skillet, over medium-high heat, heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry for 3 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove from skillet.
Heat remaining oil, stir-fry broccoli and onions for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over top of chicken-broccoli mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven at 350° until bubbling hot, about 30 minutes.

title: deer on a spear
directions: Build a charcoal fire when you start preparing.
Cut meat into small pieces 1/2-inch thick.

Place meat in plastic bag (Ziploc). Pour Dales sauce over meat. Seal bag and let set for about 30 minutes. Cut green peppers and onion into about 2 x 1-inch pieces. Cut mushrooms in half. Cut tomatoes into 1-inch wedges.
Place all ingredients on skewers with meat in between peppers, onion, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Place prepared skewers on already hot coals.
Let cook for 30 to 40 minutes, turning 3 or 4 times until done.
It's good!
I'll guarantee it.

title: texas caviar
directions: Soak peas in cold water to cover overnight.
Drain and rinse. Cover with fresh water and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or longer until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain, rinse and place drained peas in a large bowl.
Add green peppers, pimientos, onions, garlic, chiles and Italian dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 cups.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk well. Add salt, vanilla and flour. Put on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. While hot, break chocolate and place on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top, then cut into squares while hot.

title: "ma perl's" chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square cake pan. Melt chocolate and butter together in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add chips.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Cut brownies; freeze well wrapped separately.

title: caramel pie
directions: Bake pie crusts light and cool.
Mix together coconut, pecans and margarine; toast lightly, set aside and cool.
Mix Eagle Brand, Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Pour 1/2 mix in each pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 coconut mixture next; then drizzle caramel on top.
Repeat, layering ingredients.
This pie may be wrapped and frozen.
Set out of freezer and thaw a few minutes before serving.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Combine graham cracker crumbs with baking powder.
Add this alternately with milk to cream mixture.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and put on roast.
Cook in crock-pot or bake at 350° for 2 hours in a browning bag until very tender.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer as written.
Spread salad dressing on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, toss mixture around good and serve. Good.

title: cracker candy
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Line with crackers.
Bring butter and sugar to boil, then cook 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake 5 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes, then spread chocolate evenly.
Place in refrigerator for chocolate to harden.
Pull foil off back and break into pieces.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix egg, softened margarine and cake mix.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Finely chop onion, garlic and whole tomatoes.
Heat stock pot on stove.
When pot is hot, add the olive oil; saute onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Add thyme, oregano, basil and bouillon.
Saute for about 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and chopped whole tomatoes, along with the sugar and bay leaves.
Brown hamburger; drain off excess grease.
Add to sauce. Add water.
Let simmer for at least 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: lime cubes
directions: Prepare the Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into cubes.
Spoon into 4 dessert glasses and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in large jar or similar airtight container.
(Use 2 teaspoons per cup hot water.)

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir 2 1/2 cups oats into dry mixture.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture.
Pat 2/3 dough in 15 x 10-inch greased pan.
Put chocolate chips, condensed milk and 2 tablespoons margarine in microwave-safe medium bowl and heat 1 1/2 minutes until smooth.
Stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour fudge over dough.
Dot with rest of dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hungarian butterhorns
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Stir in dry yeast.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg yolks, 2 teaspoons vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Beat egg whites in mixing bowl until stiff peaks form.
Add 3/4 cup sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in walnuts.
Divide dough into 4 portions.
Roll 1 portion at a time into circle on surface sprinkled with confectioners sugar and granulated sugar. Spread each circle with 1/4 of the filling.
Cut into wedges. Roll from wide ends to enclose filling.
Place point side down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Combine milk, shortening and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Cover; let rise until bubbly.
Add eggs and sugar mixed with spices.
Mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to make dough that can be kneaded.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into doughnuts.
Let raise on doughboard until double in bulk.

title: lo-cal coffee liqueur chocolate cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle wafer crumbs in the bottom of an 8-inch pan.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, blend all ingredients except the egg and mini morsels until smooth (blender preferred).
Add egg and mix until blended.
Fold in the chocolate morsels.
Pour the entire mixture over crumbs in the pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes until the cake is set.
Let cool.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Transfer to a serving flat platter.
Garnish with mint sprigs, chocolate curls or strawberries.

title: city chicken
directions: You will need 10 to 12 wooden skewers.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Melt over hot water or in microwave the butterscotch chips and butter or margarine.

Remove from heat and beat in the brown sugar and egg. Sift together the flour and soda. Add to mixture and beat well. Add the nuts and vanilla. Chill until it can be handled. Shape into 2 rolls. Wrap in waxed paper. Chill in refrigerator or freeze.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk and flour alternately.
Dissolve soda in remainder of buttermilk; add salt.
Add this and chocolate mixture to batter.
Beat egg whites and fold into cake batter.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Mix 4 cups of
flour,
yeast,
sugar
and salt in large bowl. Stir well and
add
shortening.
Add
hot
water to dry ingredients, all at once.
Mix
at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add 2 cups flour; mix at high speed for 1 minute.
Add remaining flour; mix by hand.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup onions in large bowl.
Pour into a shallow pre-sprayed casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top.
Bake 5 more minutes until top is brown.

title: granny's quick fudge frosting
directions: Stir together and bring to full rolling boil.
Boil hard just 3 minutes.
Cool slightly and beat in 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar (sifted) and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
May need a little more powdered sugar.

title: veal, turkey or chicken marsala
directions: On bread board, mix 2 teaspoons flour and pepper.
Dredge cutlets in this.
Melt oleo in heavy frying pan.
Saute cutlets about 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer to platter and keep warm. In same heavy frying pan, add rest of flour to pan drippings. Stir.
Add broth and wine.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Spoon over cutlets.
Serves 2.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Blend
cottage
cheese
with milk.
Add dry ingredients plus lemon rind
and
juice to well beaten egg yolks.
Stir in cheese and
milk.
Fold
in
stiffly
beaten egg whites.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450° then reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 more minutes.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 cups dry mixture.

title: christmas party dip
directions: Pick through crab meat to remove any shell fragments.
In a bowl, put crab meat, finely crushed package of Knorr onion soup, diced, spiced shrimp and container of sour cream.
Blend together well and refrigerate.
Wash and cut up vegetables and mushrooms into serving pieces.
Arrange on party tray around dip and serve.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs with oil in bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in zucchini, onions and shredded cheese.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a large skillet, cook the beef until well done and no pink is showing; drain. Chop up cheese and add to the beef. Stir over medium heat until cheese is melted. Stir in the salsa. Off heat, add the sour cream and combine well. If too thick, add some of the salsa liquid. Serve hot with nachos. The "scoop" type is best.

title: potato soup
directions: Put in boiler and add water to cover veggies.
Cover and cook until veggies are soft.
Add milk, salt, pepper, parsley and eggs. Cover and continue to simmer for about 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add 2 teaspoons margarine.
Serve hot.

title: cracker salad
directions: Chop celery, pepper, onion and eggs.
Mix with soup, mayonnaise and broken up crackers.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 12-cup muffin tins or mini-muffin tins.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Whisk oil, milk, eggs and extract in another large bowl until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix only until evenly moistened.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: cookie sheet chocolate cake
directions: Sift together soda, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Melt and bring to a rapid boil the oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.

title: poppy seed casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook the ground turkey, onion and green pepper until the meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Drain; stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions; drain.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs 3 minutes.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat well.
Stir in softened margarine.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake one hour.
Cool. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: How do you make homemade ice cream without an ice cream maker? Kick the can!
Also known as Roll-the-Can ice cream.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Defrost broccoli and squeeze water out.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put chicken breast in next.
Mix soup, lemon juice and Miracle Whip.
Pour over chicken.
Break up toasted bread in small pieces.
Put over soup, then add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in greased flat baking dish.
Heat soup, water, rice and soup mix.
Pour over chicken. Add cheese over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except broccoli.
Put cooked broccoli in buttered casserole dish and pour mixture over all. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle a little flour on pecans.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, Karo and margarine together.
Add vanilla and pecans. Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: quick and easy banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas and eggs.
Add biscuit mix and nuts by hand. Stir until mix is moistened well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: cornmeal soup
directions: Boil chicken, oleo, celery, onions, salt and pepper.
Remove from stock; cool.
Debone chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup, deboned chicken and sprinkle cornmeal into boiling soup a pinch at a time while stirring.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour cereal into large bowl.
Heat peanut butter and margarine to boiling in 1-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Pour over cereal; toss until evenly coated.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Stir in pretzels, raisins and nuts.
Spread on waxed paper.
Cool 2 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of a 9-inch pie plate. Top with chili.
Sprinkle cheeses on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bread pudding
directions: Warm milk and honey together.
Prepare bread cubes, removing crust.
Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs slightly with salt; add to bread cubes with honey mixture and vanilla.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Heat oven to 300°.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
May be served warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: favorite one-egg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour two 8 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans or a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan.
Into large bowl of electric mixer, sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and milk.
At medium speed, beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping side of bowl and guiding mixture into beaters with rubber scraper.
Add egg and vanilla; beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour batter into prepared pans; bake layers 25 to 30 minutes, square, 30 to 35 minutes, or until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertip.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans; cool thoroughly on wire racks.
Fill and frost as desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump first 3 ingredients into shallow 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with dry cake mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until crusty and golden brown.

title: pears and cheese
directions: Drain pear halves. Arrange on plate. Take a tsp. of miracle whip and put in center of pear. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: tuno casserole
directions: Put Tuno in food processor for a few rounds to make Tuno flakey.
Mix all ingredients with Tuno.
Cover over with cheese or cracker mill.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: deer roast
directions: Cook deer roast.
Cook first 11 ingredients (except deer roast) until thickens, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and capers.
Serve over thin sliced deer.

title: plantation bars
directions: Melt almond bark.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and peanuts.
Stir well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring in a bowl; mix well.
In a separate bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar and gently fold into the milk and lemon juice mixture. Pour into the prepared crust.
Chill for 3 1/2 hours or until set.

title: escalloped salmon
directions: Butter or spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Fill dish 1-inch deep with cracker crumbs, crusty sourdough, herbal bread or whatever you have on hand. Flake over a layer of home canned salmon. Add a layer of sweet onion and diced celery. Put another layer of bread. Layer cheese if you like. Pour milk (fat-free is fine) until halfway up the dish. Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°, covered. Remove foil to crisp up top.

title: vegetable souffle
directions: Scald milk with margarine in saucepan.
Stir in bread remove from heat, add eggs mixing well.
Arrange vegetables in greased baking dish, pour milk mixture over top.
Top with cheese, bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake by package instructions.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: steak sinkiang
directions: Heat oil; add garlic.
Saute beef until nearly well-done; remove from oil.
Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Add cornstarch to cold water in a separate cup; mix until smooth. Pour over vegetables and stir until thickened.
Add beef and bean sprouts.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Sift or use slotted spoon to mix.
Store in glass jar.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Add soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir in potatoes and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peachy punch for a bunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well until sugar dissolves. Makes 6 gallons.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Combine strawberries and cornstarch until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Reserve 1/3 cup, and cool.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Funnel used should have about 1/2-inch opening.
Special ones are available in Ocean City or in Pennsylvania Dutch areas. However, not really necessary.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer all vegetables in chicken broth.
Add 3 cups milk when vegetables are tender.
Bring to boil.
Add 1/2 cup milk with flour and butter.
Heat slightly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: snickers pie
directions: In a double boiler or heavy boiler, melt together Snickers bars, peanut butter and half and half.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip; pour chocolate syrup on top and enjoy.
It's great and easy!

title: neysa's stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle flavor crystals over ground beef.
In large skillet, brown beef; crumble and drain fat.
Add flour, milk, onion flakes and onion soup mix.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sour cream and cook on low heat for another 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable burritos
directions: Saute vegetables (onion and garlic first).
Top with grated cheese and bake until bubbly.
Serve with warm tortillas, salsa, sour cream and guacamole.
Can put cheese on the table instead of melting on top.

title: non cooked play dough("best play dough in world")
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in water, oil, food coloring (1/2 bottle for vivid color).
Knead until smooth.
Add more flour, if needed.
Store in airtight container.

title: five star dip for veggies
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients except oatmeal and mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done, about 15 minutes.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Combine oil, sugar and vinegar; beat with wire whisk until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Three-quarter cup of mayonnaise may be added to make Thousand Island dressing.

title: pepper pizza
directions: Fry banana peppers in oil until half done.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Simmer until done, about 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking

soda, cut in shortening. Add milk and stir. Knead lightly on floured board, roll to 1/8 inch thick. Divide dough into 8 parts. Fill hollow of apples with 1 Tbls. sugar and 1 Tbls. butter. Fold dough over apples and press edges together, place in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with
sugar and cinnamon mix and dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: 2 day cucumber pickles (lime)
directions: Dissolve lime in water, stir until dissolved. Soak cucumbers in solution for 24 hours. Remove and wash 4 times. Mix vinegar, sugar, and salt in jar together for later. Put spices in cloth bag, place in bottom of pan. Put cucumbers on top of spices and pour on vinegar, sugar, and salt solution. Soak overnight. Boil 15 minutes. Put cucumbers in and seal.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar with cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Make pudding according to directions on package.
Spread pudding mix on crust.
Top with Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: upside-down pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cake mix, nuts and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin.
Sprinkle nuts over the top evenly.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If not done at the end of an hour, turn off oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Mix together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine first six ingredients thoroughly with 1 can tomato sauce.
Pack firmly into an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Pour second can of tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake 20 minutes more until loaf is glazed.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain corn into baking dish.
Beat egg in with corn.
Stir in crumbs.
Pour milk over and dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: spinach maria
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach according to package directions and drain off all excess water when done.
Saut onion in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, together.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Slightly beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl; add pudding.
Mix. Beat with wire whisk. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of cookies and rocks into mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies. Freeze until firm.

title: easy loaf of bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dough will be stiff.
Put in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or Pyrex loaf pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not knead mixture.

title: aunt jo's ginger cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix the shortening with the brown sugar.
Add the egg and mix.
Add the dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Roll into 2 (1 1/2-inch) logs. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Slice thinly, 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container. To keep the cookies from getting too crisp, place a slice of bread in the container.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Drain juices from orange slices and pineapple.
(Should have 2 cups; if not, add enough water to make 2 cups.) Heat juices to boiling.
Mix dry jello with the juices.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fold in the fruit, then melted ice cream.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Do not beat.
Put in a large bowl.
Just stir until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done. Bake in tube pan.
Delicious.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and chill.

title: surprise cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch dish, spread pie filling.
Sprinkle pineapple over this.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Top with coconut.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: steak and noodles
directions: Brown steak in pan, then add mushrooms and juice, water and soup mix.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in sour cream and flour; bring to a boil once more.
Simmer for 15 minutes and serve over egg noodles.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix,
milk and cheese until a soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
These taste a lot like Red Lobster's biscuits.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, milk and pudding.
Chill 5 minutes.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on box.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Cut cake into squares.
Layer cake, strawberries and pudding mixture into bowl. Chill until sets.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for an hour.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.

title: becky's belspring cheese steak sandwiches
directions: Break frozen Steak-umm in half lengthwise, then break into bite-size pieces.
Place in a large skillet and cook until all pink leaves meat.
Drain grease.
Add onion and green pepper, return to heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion and green pepper are tender, but not mushy.
Add mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Cook until mushrooms are heated.
Lay on top of the meat mixture Velveeta cheese.
When cheese starts to melt, stir thoroughly throughout the meat mixture until all of the cheese is melted.
Serve on sub buns with mayonnaise, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in pieces and serve hot or room temperature.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In medium bowl mix rice, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture, sprinkle with paprika.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and return to oven for 10 minutes longer to brown chops.

title: tropical sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and pierce fresh potatoes.
Place in a microproof 3-quart casserole with 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and microwave on High for 15 to 17 minutes, or until soft, rearranging once.
Cool enough to handle.
Peel and cut into chunks.
Place potatoes and margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Beat with electric mixer or mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread out evenly in casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 10 minutes, stirring once.

title: potato bake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup oleo, soup and sour cream together.
Pour over other ingredients, except corn flakes and melted oleo, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
