Top this mixture with cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to
Bake on ungreased cookie sheeet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool a minute or two before removing.

title: oriental meat loaf
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 10 x 5-inch slightly round loaf in a 2 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with waxed paper. Microwave at High for 14 to 18 minutes or until firm to touch.
Turn dish a half turn after 7 minutes.
Drain off excess dripping. (Note:
Use a custard cup to keep the ring shaped loaf in shape during cooking.)

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Warm the buttermilk.
Add yeast and oil.
Mix well. Add sugar, egg and flour (more if needed). Roll out at once and cut biscuits.
Brush with butter.
Fold over and let rise 1 hour or until raised.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Roughly chop the beef.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook briefly without browning. Stir in milk and bring to boiling, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with a few drops of Tabasco and some ground black pepper. Stir in chipped beef and heat thoroughly.
Serve over toast or baked potato. Serves 2 to 4.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Combine and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Frost with Cool Whip (or top with Cool Whip as you serve). Bake at 350° until done. Follow directions on cake mix box for length of time for that size pan.

title: wild blueberry crisp
directions: Combine blueberries, apples, sugar and lemon. Place in an 8x8x2 inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, flour, pecan pieces and rolled oats in a large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread mixture over blueberries.
Bake at 325° until topping is golden and filling bubbles, about 65 minutes for frozen berries and 45 minutes for fresh.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
8 servings.

title: filled icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs, beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix and roll out 1/2 inch thick and spread with filling.

title: roller coasters
directions: Lay one slice cheese on one slice ham.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Serve as finger food.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, garlic powder and grated cheese.
Saute onions in butter.
Layer in casserole dish: noodles, potato mixture, onions and noodles again on top.
Add more onions and butter over all.
Cover with foil or lid and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, saving some of the tomato sauce. Put in a loaf pan or shape in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour and re-measure.
Add other dry ingredients.
Add cranberries and nuts last.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: fudge sunday pie
directions: Make up to 1 week ahead.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In 9-inch pie plate with hand, mix nuts, brown sugar and 3 tablespoons butter/oleo.
Press mixture onto bottom of pan and sides.
Bake 8 minutes; cool crust.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Bake in large slightly oiled sheet cake pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.
We like ours covered with a thin glaze of butter frosting.

title: lemon lush or chocolate
directions: First Layer:
Mix the butter, flour and nuts together and spread on pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop in hot fat.
Brown both sides until done.

title: frozen pink sweet strawberry salad
directions: Mix all and freeze.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat the yolks until light and lemon colored; set aside.
Mix the sugar and salt together thoroughly.
Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add the sugar mixture to the milk; beat until free of lumps.
Add 3 tablespoons of the hot milk mixture to the egg yolk mixture, then add the yolks to the hot milk.
Beat again until thoroughly mixed.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until the mixture has thickened and coats the spoon. Remove from the heat; allow to cool slightly.

title: sunshine fruit parfait
directions: In small bowl combine orange juice and sugar, mix well.
Fold in cool whip and lightly beat.
In another small bowl combine orange pieces, bananas, and pineapple.
In parfait glasses alternately layer fruit, coconut and cool whip.
Chill.
Serves 2 (may be doubled).

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add next four ingredients gradually.
Stir in sugar, cranberries and nuts, gently mixing well.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: granola
directions: Put oats, wheat germ, sugar, coconut, almonds and cinnamon in a large nonmetal bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Set aside.
Slice banana into 1 cup measuring cup and mash until smooth.
Add oil and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over oat mixture and stir.
Place in microwave.
Set on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook again for 3 minutes.
Stir and cook again for 2 more minutes. Stir in dried fruit/nuts.
Cool for 1 hour.
Cover in airtight container.
Good for up to 2 weeks.

title: sweet cinnamon butter
directions: Mix together until blended well. Serve with fresh warm bread or rolls.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough around a greased pizza pan.
Bake as directed on cookie package, but do not over cook.
Take out and let cool slightly.
Cream sugar and cream cheese and spread on cookie dough.
Layer fruit on top of cream cheese and drizzle with melted chocolate or vanilla almond bark.
Refrigerate 15 minutes and then ready to serve.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, but onions and celery in bacon drippings.
Saute until tender.
Put all ingredients in peas except rice.
Bring to boil and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Then put in rice.

title: bachelor's brunch casserole
directions: Brown and drain the sausage.
In a greased casserole dish, alternate layers of bread cubes, sausage and cheese, in that order, until all are used.
Add eggs to milk and mix.
Add salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Mix well and pour over layers slowly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in a 350°
oven.
Serves 6.

title: frozen rainbow delight
directions: Whip the cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crushed macaroons and nuts.
Spread half of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with alternate small spoonfuls of sherbet so that some of each color/flavor will be in each serving.
Top with remaining cream mixture, smoothing out and freeze.
Serves 10 to 16.

title: luck of the irish truffles
directions: Place wax paper on tray.
Break candy bar into pieces. In small saucepan, stir together whipping cream, sugar and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat. Immediately add candy pieces and vanilla. Stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is well blended.
Pour into glass 9 inch pie plate. Cover, refrigerate several hours or overnight to ripen and harden.
Form into 3/4 inch balls, working quickly to prevent melting. Roll in sprinkles. Place on prepared tray.
Cover, refrigerate 2 hours until firm. Store, covered in refrigerator. Makes 3 1/2 dozen candies.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Mix all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to low.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Add Hershey bars, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread in buttered pan; cool.
Slice to desired size.

title: venison jerky
directions: Remove all fat and place meat in the freezer.
When the meat is semi-frozen, slice into 1/4 inch strips (the thinner the slice, the faster the drying).
Meat cut with the grain will be chewy while meat cut against the grain will be tender and break more easily when dried.
Mix all ingredients and marinate the meat for at least 1 hour, then drain in a colander.
Place meat on trays to dry.
For faster drying do not overlap meat.
Turn meat over at least once during the drying period.
Dry at 145° for 8 to 10 hours.
It is dry when it bends like a green willow without breaking.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp and salad
directions: Cook peas and cool.
Clean and rinse shrimp.
Mix rice, peas and shrimp with salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Chill.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, place all ingredients, except chips and Monterey Jack cheese.
Stir well.
Place chips standing up in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: big bean pot
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven, cook and stir bacon and onions until bacon is crisp and onions are tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given; mix well.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown and set.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour, Crisco and salt together until crumbly.
Add liquid.
Blend with fork.
Makes 5 to 6 crusts.
Can be frozen.

title: orange carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, carrots and flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Frost while cookies are warm.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir well and set aside.
Grease bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan with butter.
Add crumb mixture; tilt pan to coat side and bottom.
Chill.

title: next best thing to a prize winning animal!
directions: Blend flour, butter and 1/2 of the pecans.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend 1/2 of the Cool Whip with cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on top of cooled crust. Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip, nuts and grated Hershey bar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate fudge sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Re-sift with sugar, salt and cinnamon. Put butter, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, put beaten eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to other mixture and mix well. Bake in a greased and floured 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Start the icing the last 5 minutes cake is cooking.

title: reuben dip
directions: Chop and mix corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Mix mayo, horseradish and dressing; add to corned beef mixture.
Place in a flat 9 or 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with rye crackers or party rye bread as a dip or spread.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake to package directions.
Pour pineapple and its juice into a saucepan with the sugar and cook until slightly thickened.
Keep hot.
When cake comes from the oven, poke holes all over the top.
Pour hot pineapple over the hot cake.
Chill cake in refrigerator.
When cake is cold, prepare instant vanilla pudding and add the coconut; spread over cake.
Spread the Cool Whip over the pudding and then sprinkle walnuts all over.
Keep in refrigerator for safe keeping, covered with plastic wrap.
Serves 12 large pieces or 15 smaller.

title: double chocolate nuggets
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and eggs. Stir in chocolate chips.
Top each cookie with a pecan half. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: theresa's pie crust(makes 2 crusts)
directions: Mix well; sprinkle 3 tablespoons water over mixture and gather into a ball.
Do not add more water, just oil if necessary.
Roll out between 2 pieces of waxed paper, loosening waxed paper when necessary.
No flour mess with this crust and it's very good. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: magnolia treats(a nice substitute for mimosas for brunch)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Serve over ice. Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 6 cups.

title: harvard beets
directions: Add vinegar (or lemon juice) and water to combined sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and boil about 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer to heat through, about 1/2 hour.
Add butter, salt and pepper to season.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan so they don't touch.
Chop onions and scatter over chicken.
Mix together soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes. Sprinkle about 1/4 cup sliced almonds over chicken for the last 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: french lemon bars
directions: Mix 1 3/4 cups flour, pinch of salt and powdered sugar.
Melt shortening and pour over mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan, leave a slight raised edge.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and cumin.
Drain.
In 2-quart microwave dish put crushed chips and pour on tomato sauce. Spread beans (may need to add a little water to beans to make spreadable) on sauce.
Then add ground beef and 1 cup of cheese. Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes in microwave.
Top with sour cream, lettuce and cheese.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until cooked.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly until cheese is melted.

title: low-fat corn oil pastry
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. With fork or pastry knife cut in oil, then ice water, a tablespoon at a time, until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
Double recipe for more or larger crust.

title: almond pancake mix
directions: In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well blended. Store in a resealable plastic bag. Yield: about 7 1/2 cups of pancake mix; enough for 3 batches of pancakes.

title: chili
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, onion mix and chili mix.
Stir. Then add tomato juice and sauce.
Stir and cook slowly about 2 hours, stirring often.
Add beans and red pepper if you want them after about 1 hour.
If you choose to use regular onion, saute and cook with meat.

title: baked home fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; layer in baking dish.
Layer onion, margarine and black pepper.
Fill baking dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown crust on edges and top.

title: chewy fudge brownies
directions: Mix together
flour,
sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs and melted margarine
last.
This makes them chewy rather than like cake.
Bake
in 350° oven until done (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: hot mulled cider
directions: To cider or juice, add brown sugar. Stir until dissolved. Place cloves and cinnamon sticks in coffee basket. Brew as for coffee. Serve hot.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill overnight.
Form in small balls and roll in sugar.
Do not press down.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand in pan for 30 to 60 seconds.
For soft cookies, bake 8 minutes.
For crispier cookies, bake 10 minutes. Cookies will crack on top.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: easy strawberry ice cream
directions: Slice berries.
Put in food processor and puree berries.
Set aside 10 minutes to get thick.
In a medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice; set aside for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, with an electric mixer, beat cream until peaks.
Fold milk mixture into cream to thicken.
Fold in berries.
Pack mixture into a freezer container and freeze until firm or overnight.

title: melt away cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, powdered sugar, oil and margarine.
Then add vanilla and eggs and beat again.
Then add dry ingredients: flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Mix again.

title: ground meat scramble
directions: Brown ground meat.
Do not drain.
Add salt, pepper and flour. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Toast your bread while this cooks.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.
Pour gravy over toast.
Serve.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown about 30 minutes.
Cut into rectangular shapes, about 2 x 1-inches. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 4 dozen.
Bon appetit!

title: pasta sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over your favorite "macaroni".

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat bottom and sides of an 8-inch baking dish with oil.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, coating surface evenly.
Beat eggs.
Drain spinach well.
Add spinach and cheeses to eggs; mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into prepared dish. Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: steak bake
directions: Layer one tablespoon margarine, 1/2 of soup mix and steak in a casserole.
Top with remaining soup mix and margarine.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: microwave cauliflower and carrot quiche
directions: In
1 quart bowl combine cauliflower, carrot and water. Cover with
plastic
wrap.
Cook at High 6 to 7 minutes.	Stir once. Sprinkle
vegetables
into	pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Pour
cream
into
cup measure.
Cook at Medium 2 to 2 1/4 minutes.

title: cocktail rye pizza appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture on slice of cocktail rye.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
This mix can be prepared the night before.

title: apricot strudel
directions: Cut as pie crust.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Divide into 2 parts. Roll out to about 12 x 10-inches.
Spread with apricot jam, coconut and chopped nuts.
Roll as jelly roll.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and pecans
directions: Brown chicken and add stock, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Remove chicken from pan and defat liquid.
Reduce sauce, then add cream and pecans.
Return chicken to the pan.
Serve with pecans on top of chicken.
Serves 4.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: underwood chicken spread
directions: Mix with mixer but don't overmix. Serve with crackers or on toast. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice medley
directions: Amount of each depends on number of servings.

title: light chicken and pasta salad
directions: In blender, puree first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in orange zest.
Stir in chicken, tomato and parsley.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: party punch no. 2
directions: Dilute lemonade and orange juice with water and chill.
Place scoops of sherbet and ice cream in bottom of punch bowl, then add juice mixture.

title: whipped jello
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Let set until thick. Whip milk; add lemon juice, rind and sugar.
When thickened, add jello.
Top with graham crackers, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt the butter in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 egg and cake mix in a bowl (this is a very dry mixture).
Sprinkle this over the melted butter in the 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar until smooth. Pour this mixture on top of the cake mixture.
Spread it to completely cover the cake mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Allow to cool at least 20 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling on bottom of pan.
Spoon in pineapple and juice and sprinkle cake mix over it.
Add pecans and slice margarine over other layer.
Spread brown sugar on top.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 325° for about an hour.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Stir melted butter and brown sugar together.
Add corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Line 9-inch pie pan with 2/3 mixture.
Fill with 1 quart slightly softened ice cream.
Sprinkle rest of mixture on top and press lightly into ice cream.
Freeze several hours or overnight.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine all juices in bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and orange slices.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil piece of beef.
When about half done, put in one-half cup of rice.
When rice is done, take scant teacup flour, one egg, one-half teaspoon baking powder and make soft batter. Drop into broth with a spoon.
In that put one small onion and about six whole cloves.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook a few minutes.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fit 12 muffin cups with paper liners. Coat each with cooking spray.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: janis o's onion casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot holiday punch
directions: Combine sugars and apple cider in a large saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until sugars are dissolved.
Add cloves and cinnamon stick.
Boil over medium heat for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to simmer and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Add grapefruit and orange juices. Heat, but do not boil.
Strain and empty into heatproof punch bowl. Decorate the orange slices with maraschino cherries and cloves. Ready to serve.
Yields approximately 8 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Mix water and Jell-O together; stir to dissolve and let thicken.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
When Jell-O thickens, add cranberry mixture. Refrigerate.

title: fast microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn.
Remove any "old maids" from popcorn.
Combine other ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes once it has started.
Put popcorn into a (clean) large "grocery" bag.
Pour caramel mixture over popcorn.

title: weinberg's sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage, drain. Mix cream cheese and Rotel. Heat. Add sausage, mix well. Serve hot with your choice of chips.

title: jan hagel (dutch)
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend flour and cinnamon. Add to butter mixture.
Pat into lightly greased 15 x 10-inch pan. Beat water and egg white until frothy.
Brush over dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until very lightly browned.
Cut immediately into 3 x 1-inch strips.

title: english shrimp puffs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until soft.
Cut English muffins in half and put on a cookie tray.
Spread mixture on evenly.
Put in freezer for an hour (or store there until day of serving).
Take out and cut into 8 sections.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan to drain.
Put onion, celery and bell pepper in bacon fat; brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, black pepper, Tabasco sauce and salt. Cook slowly until thick, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp 30 minutes before serving.
Break bacon into small pieces; add last. Go by taste; add more seasoning if needed.
(One little pinch of sugar helps.)

title: pork roast
directions: Place roast in pan.
Add a small piece of dried red pepper, salt to taste and a pinch of sage.
Cover with water; place on top of stove and cook on medium heat until done.
Take out of pan and place in a baking dish.
Pour a small amount of vinegar over roast, then put a small amount of black pepper over roast.
Brown in a 400° oven.
Serve hot or cold.

title: preschool pizza
directions: Give each child a cookie.
Have prepared mixture of cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Smooth on cookie.
Arrange sliced fruit on tray.
Let each child top pizza as desired.
They may want to make faces or try to make their cookie look like a real pizza.
Get creative!
Top with shredded coconut, if desired.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Crumble cornbread and mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken, onion and green pepper until done.
Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Eat.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Put fruit, margarine, sugar, spice and water in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour, bicarbonate of soda and salt.
Beat well.
Pour into a 6 inch greased and lined cake tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: healthy salad dressing
directions: Blend everything in blender.
Makes enough for a couple of weeks.
Refrigerate.

title: polish sausage, potatoes and cabbage
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up.
Place in large pot.
Fill halfway with water.
Cut up cabbage and put in pot.
Cut Polish sausage in pieces and place in pot.
Cook for 1 hour on top of stove.
One meal altogether.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed except omit butter; cool.
Add onions, pepper, olives and artichokes.
Combine marinade, curry and mayonnaise.
Add dressing to rice and chill.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cobbler or peach cobbler
directions: Drain berries. Keep 1 cup juice. Cream all together. Pour into greased square pan.
Spoon fruit over batter and pour juice over all. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp antipasto
directions: Place shrimp, cheese and olives in large shallow pan.
In pint jar, combine remaining ingredients, except salami and pepper; shake well.
Pour over shrimp.
Cover, refrigerate, 6 hours or overnight, stirring constantly.
Add salami and pepper.
Toss. Drain.
Garnish as desired.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients.
Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon on half of the meat mixture.
Mix the cottage cheese with egg, then layer 1 cup of cheese mixture on top of meat mixture.
Repeat the layers again, using 2 cups cottage cheese in all.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on broiler pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove.
Add to tomato sauce.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast, milk and sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
In bowl, put flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in Crisco and liquid.
Knead until smooth; roll out about 3/4-inch thick and cut place in greased pan.
Brush with butter.
Let rise 30 minutes or until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Add sugar, salt and butter to warm potatoes.
Add crushed pineapple and nutmeg. Mix well.
Pour in buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and arrange marshmallows on top of potatoes, 1/2-inch apart.
Return to oven and brown.

title: appetizer fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Turn into 2 (3-cup) freezer trays. Freeze firm.

title: german cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onions in butter.
Add flour; stir.
Slowly add broth and heat over low heat until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.

title: best beer batter ever
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika; add beer slowly to make a smooth batter.
Batter can be used for shrimp, oysters, fish, chicken and turkey pieces.
Flour items in a bag, dip in batter and deep fry in hot oil (375°).
Fry shrimp, 3 minutes; oysters, 4 minutes; fish, depending on size and chicken and turkey to a golden brown.

title: pineapple rum flambe
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar over med heat. Add pineapples; reduce heat to low. Cook 4 more min. Then cook on the other side of slice until soft. Add rum and flambe, stay clear of the flames.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute garlic, shallot and crushed red pepper in butter in a Dutch oven for 2 minutes.
Add milk and next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Add potatoes; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Swiss and Parmesan cheeses.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes; beat them.
Add sour cream, margarine, garlic and salt; pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Heat oil with seasonings (do not boil) and pour over crackers. An easy snack!

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Layer tomato slices, basil and onion in pie shell. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: stir-fry pineapple turkey
directions: Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and water; stir well. Toss turkey chunks in cornstarch mixture.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup syrup.
In wok or medium skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil.
Saute onion 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove onion to a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet; saute celery and water chestnuts 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add to onion.

title: spinach souffl
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Whip eggs and milk together.
Whip egg whites together.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over cooked spinach in 9 x 13 glass dish.
Stir in egg whites and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can substitute kale or broccoli for spinach.

title: barbecue slaw - eastern carolina
directions: Grate cabbage in a large bowl. Combine all other ingredients and mix well. Chill for 1 hour before serving. Makes about 20 servings.

title: sauerkraut and apples
directions: Combine sauerkraut, fat, water, apples and onion.
Cook slowly until apples are tender.
Add salt, sugar, caraway seed and potatoes.
Continue
cooking
minutes or until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: alma ivie's chili
directions: Cook meat before adding other ingredients.
Cook for about 35 minutes.

title: creole franks
directions: Brown wieners, onion, and pepper in skillet with margarine on med. high heat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook on high until steam appears, then turn on low for 15 mins.
Serve over rice.

title: tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Slice thin and place by layers in a salad bowl, omitting onion, if not liked.
Add dash of cayenne pepper, salt and vinegar to taste.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix dates, soda and hot water; let stand.
Mix 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs, flour and salt.
Add to date mixture.
Mix well and put into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix chocolate chips, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts; put on top of cake mix.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain off liquid from the sauerkraut, put sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Heat this to a rolling boil.
To the drained kraut add onion, celery, green pepper and pimento.
Add the heated liquid to the vegetables; stir until blended.
Leave for 24 hours to improve flavor.
This keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix 3/4 cup vinegar, water, oil, salt, black pepper and sugar. Boil and set aside to cool.
Pour over peas, pimentos, Shoepeg corn, celery, green pepper and green onions.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, soup, milk, onion and chili peppers.
In greased 2-quart casserole, place a layer of tortillas, layer of chicken mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese.
Add Bisquick and paprika.
Blend well. Roll into balls about 1-inch in size.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: grandma honeywell's lemonade cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine flour and soda; alternately add lemonade and flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets. Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Brush with remaining lemonade when removed from oven.

title: sour dough waffles
directions: Mix the flour, water and yeast together in a bowl; let set overnight covered.
This is the sour dough.
In the morning, beat eggs and oil into sour dough.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, salt and baking soda; add this to the dough and mix.
Pour batter on a waffle iron and cook.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and let set overnight. Make 2 layer cake from 1 box or use Bundt pan.
After cake is cool, split the layers to make four.
Put coconut topping between layers, top and side.
Wrap cake airtight.
Let refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Combine Jell-O with 3 cups of hot water.
Add pineapple.
Add frozen strawberries and mashed bananas.
Pour half of this mixture into Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate until set.
In the meantime, mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Spread on hardened Jell-O and add rest of Jell-O.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain off brine and discard.
Slice pickles crossways into large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and let stand on shelf for about 24 hours.
Can be eaten immediately after.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Press half mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with berries and rhubarb. Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and stir until blended.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and pour over strawberry rhubarb mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: dad's cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges in food processor.
Combine mixture with diced apples and sugar; stir thoroughly.
Chill. This is great for Thanksgiving and Christmas, and there's no fat!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients over high heat for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining 2 ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie tray or waxed paper.
Cool. Eat.
Enjoy.

title: quiche
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Fry onions in bacon fat.
Divide between crusts.
Layer cheese on top.
Beat together eggs, cream and seasonings.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn to 325° for 20 minutes or until set.
Freezes well after baking.
Can be cut frozen and heated as individual pieces.

title: western baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredient in a crock-pot or ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 4 hours or crock-pot on medium-low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer:
Lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese, onions, bacon and Miracle Whip.

title: salad pizza
directions: Crust:
Thaw pastry according to directions.
On lightly floured surface, roll pastry into a 12-inch circle.
Place on a large baking sheet.
Use a fork to prick bottom.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Pastry will shrink.
Cool.

title: quick muffins
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Beat egg, milk and shortening together.
Add to flour. Mix only enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: new england baked dinner
directions: Place ham in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water and cook for 1 hour.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Add cabbage and continue to cook until all the vegetables are soft, but not mushy.
Drain and serve.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears and mash; set aside.
Measure pear juice and add water to equal 2 cups.
Combine dry gelatin with cream cheese. Heat juice to boiling and pour over cream cheese stirring to dissolve gelatin and melt cheese.
Refrigerate until cool and thick.
Add mashed pears.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: bif teck marchand de vin
directions: Saute shallots and mushrooms in butter.
Blend in flour, wine, lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until liquid is reduced to 1/2 cup.
Stir in cream and simmer a few seconds longer.
Pan broil steak.
Remove steak to platter with its pan juices.
Pour on sauce and sprinkle with parsley and serve. Yield: 4 servings.

title: ben's peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix and shape into eggs.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: marian's swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into 6 or 7 pieces.
Flour pieces on both sides and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour oil in heavy skillet.
Brown steak on both sides.
Put meat in crockpot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low.
Add undiluted cream of mushroom soup and ketchup.
Cook on low until tender (approx. 2 hours).

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a large saucepan over low heat.
Let cool. Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add dry ingredients to pan.
Mix well and chill.
Form balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets to bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Mix nuts with egg white, water and nuts; add sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes; stir occasionally!

title: tahitian flower
directions: In blender, mix all ingredients except sherbet.
Divide between 4 large glasses and top with sherbet.
Garnish with orange slices, maraschino cherries and pineapple chunks on fancy toothpicks.

title: banana bread with chocolate chips
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into prepared pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool. Serves 8.

title: cold roasted chicken french-style
directions: Rub fryers with garlic and place bay leaves inside.
Mix Herb Sauce and generously coat chickens inside and out.
Also, put 1 tablespoon inside.

title: turkey on toast
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan.
Dissolve flour in butter and add milk.
Add turkey and optional additions.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve on toast, biscuit or toasted bun.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls. Combine 3 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: benlose fugle-boneless birds
directions: Pound steak; cut into 4 inch squares.
Lay on each square a small piece of bacon or sausage meat, chopped onion and spices. Roll and fasten each with a toothpick.
Brown the rolls and cover with sauce made of flour, which has been browned and to which the salt, pepper and water have been added.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Combine next 4 ingredients in bowl, blending well.
Stir in coconut.
Frost cake with coconut icing.

title: sponge drops
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add dry to wet mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on sheets for a few minutes before removing.
Cool another 5 minutes until crispy. Spread Cool Whip between 2 cookies.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate in covered container.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and celery.
Cover and boil, reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, oregano and pepper.
Blend in water; stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Stir in butter until melted.
Cut 3 slices toast in cubes; stir in tomato mixture.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut remaining slice.
Arrange down center of mixture overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 more minutes.

title: snappy turtle cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg and 1 egg yolk, beaten (reserve 1 egg white).
Blend in vanilla and maple flavoring.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly (dough will be soft). Arrange pecan halves in groups of 3 or 5 on greased sheet to resemble legs of turtle.
Mold into balls; dip bottom in unbeaten egg white and press into nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar into large bowl.
Add broccoli, bacon, onions and raisins; mix lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: red cabbage simplified(4 servings)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute lightly the onion in this.
Add sugar, wine and seed.
Add cabbage and cook covered for 20 minutes on low heat.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles in a large amount of boiling, salted water; drain.
Cook beef until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: super carrot cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together, then add dry ingredients. Add last pineapple, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased 11 x 15-inch pan.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
In large mixer bowl combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into prepared pans or pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: david's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aids with juice into a 2 gallon container.
Chill before serving.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: steak parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs, Parmesan, salt and paprika.
Dip chops into egg and roll in crumb mixture.
Heat butter and brown chops on both sides.
Cover each with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce mix, to which the tomato sauce has been added, over steak.
If sauce is too thick, add a little water.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Stir tapioca together with soup and water.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Place in 250° oven for 5 hours. Do not lift lid.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Crush wafers; cut up fruit in small pieces.
Mix wafers, fruit and nuts with milk and bourbon.
Divide into 2 to 4 pieces.
Roll pieces in confectioners sugar and wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Put in refrigerator.
Slice before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bring to boil water, oil and margarine.
Pour into flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Then add the egg whites, buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into 3 cake layer pans (prepared your way).
I use 8-inch.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, prepare the filling.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in 2-quart glass casserole container.
Beat with fork or wire whip.
Stir in broken bread slices and raisins.
Sprinkle a little more cinnamon right on the top of the pudding mixture and dot generously with butter or margarine.
Bake this mixture in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
During the baking process, the mixture will puff up.
Don't worry, it will recede after you take it out of the oven.
After you take it out of the oven, let it cool at room temperature for about 15 minutes. Refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours to solidify.

title: baked brie
directions: Unroll whole package of crescent dough and lay it flat.
Pinch perforated seams together so the dough is one piece.
Leave outer layer on Brie (white skin).
Place Brie in middle of crescent dough.
Top with brown sugar and nuts.
Fold crescent dough around Brie and pinch airtight.
Extra crescent can be cut off and made into decorations for top (i.e., leaves).
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: faye's moon cake
directions: Mix water and butter.
Bring to boil.
Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool a little.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well with a spoon or mixer.
Spread on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Don't prick.

title: sour cream coconut pound cake
directions: Mix butter, margarine and sugar.
Cream 10 minutes; add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour with soda and add alternately with sour cream.
Fold in coconut.
Add coconut flavoring.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Freezes well.

title: tortilla sandwiches
directions: Mix your cream cheese, mayo, mustard, sauce and garlic salt. Spread on tortillas.
Layer your meat and cheese (thin).
You can add things you like; I add bacon bits and black olives.
Tightly roll up.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerator overnight.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix together the crushed Oreo cookies (reserve 1/4 cup for topping) and the melted margarine.
Press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Blend together thoroughly the cream cheese, half of the Cool Whip and the powdered sugar.
Spread this mixture over the top of the cookie crumbs.

Mix the chocolate pudding as directed and spread over the cream cheese layer. Spread the remaining Cool Whip over the chocolate pudding layer and then sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup cookie crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan or shape into loaf in center of any pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients. Stir to blend. Chill for at least 1 hour. Serve in hollowed out round loaf of French bread or Hawaiian bread. Use hollowed out section to make bread cups for dipping.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high for 1 hour.
Stir in 1/2 pound bag of Doritos, coarsely crushed.
Continue cooking 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon and egg lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1/3 cup drippings.
Set bacon aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually add milk; cook until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spoon a small amount white sauce into dish.
Divide lasagna, bacon, white sauce, eggs and Swiss cheese into thirds; layer in a dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Let stand.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix together thoroughly, shortening, brown sugar, egg, stir in applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, spices, and stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by tsp. onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes.

title: perfect (and simple) salsa
directions: Chop up stewed tomatoes and whole tomatoes in a food processor.
Chop onions and jalapenos and add to tomatoes.
Add salt and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
May be stored in refrigerator or canned for future use.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in pan over medium heat.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved, then cook until a little tried in cold water forms soft ball or 236°.
Beat egg whites 2 minutes at high speed until stiff; continue beating and pour 1/2 of syrup over beaten egg whites.
Continue beating while cooking rest of syrup until it forms hard ball or 264°.
Add this syrup gradually to syrup and egg mixture you have been beating.
Add vanilla and continue beating until candy is thick enough to drop from spoon. Place on buttered platter.
Chopped nuts may be added just before candy is ready to spoon.

title: zucchini pea soup
directions: Saute zucchini in butter.
Combine all ingredients and cook until done; cool.
Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Reheat and serve with dollop of sour cream (optional).

title: hot punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and serve.
Makes 2 quarts.
Other flavors of Jell-O may be used as a substitute for the strawberry Jell-O.

title: death by chocolate dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan according to box directions. Cool and break up into pieces.
Make pudding with milk.
Break up Skor or Heath bars into small pieces.

Layer in a deep pan (9 x 13-inch) four layers of each of the ingredients, starting with the cake pieces pressed down (1/4); spread pudding over that (1/4); spread Cool Whip (1/4) over that and then add the candy bars (1/4).
Makes a 4 tier dessert.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in ovenproof 4-quart pan. Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° (remove cover for last 30 minutes). Good as side dish or main dish.

title: hommus tahini(mid eastern recipe)
directions: Rinse chickpeas with cold water.
Put in pan and cover with water; boil for a few minutes until soft and drain.
Put chickpeas, tahini, garlic, lemon juice and salt in a blender and blend until smooth.
You can put homos in a shallow dish and serve with wedges of flat bread.
You can sprinkle red pepper and cumin over top, if desired.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of the chocolate in a heavy saucepan, until melted, with butter.
Beat or mix cream cheese and sugar. Stir in whipped topping until smooth, spoon into crust and freeze until firm.

title: lazy day vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, add all ingredients.
Addition of salt is not necessary because of the canned vegetables.
To lower the salt content further, use no salt canned vegetables.
Add water to desired consistency.
Bring to a boil for several minutes, then lower heat and continue to simmer for several hours.
Very hardy winter soup.

title: fried chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings.
In bowl or doubled lunch bags, put flour, salt and paprika.
Add chicken wings and shake well.
Fry in skillet with depth so the chicken can be deep fried.
Wings will float when done.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain.
Pour into bottom of casserole dish. Next, add 2 cans of black-eyed peas, including juice.
Add jar of salsa.
Last, add cornbread mix, as prepared on box.
Bake at 350° until bread is brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian nut patties
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in food processor; add the eggs, seasoning, garlic and cream cheese.
Form into long patties and fry lightly.
Pour mushroom soup that has been diluted over the patties.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 18 patties.

title: banana pudding 1
directions: Layer cookies and cut up bananas in a bowl.
In a sauce pan mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
When mixed well, add flour mix until creamy.
Pour in milk and cook on medium heat until thick.
Needs to be somewhat thick but still creamy enough to pour onto bananas and cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Drain, then mix all ingredients together.
Put into buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: May substitute whole wheat flour.
Add enough to make a drop cookie.
When using white flour, can be used as a rolled cookie. Mix in order of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: four-fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and orange juice; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add raisins and apricots.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes, or until apricots are almost tender, stirring often.
Stir in cranberries, prunes and vanilla; cool.

title: j.p.'s cheese dip
directions: Put in microwavable bowl and heat on High for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with your favorite foods.

title: lemon curd
directions: In the top of a double boiler, combine the sugar, butter, lemon juice and lemon rind; mix well.
Place the pan directly over the heat, stirring constantly, and cook until the sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan large enough for batter to be thin.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine the flour and rolled oats.
Cut in the margarine until the mixture is crumbly; mix in 1/3 cup sugar.
Set aside for topping.
Drain cherries reserving the juice.
Combine the remaining sugar with the cornstarch, spices and lemon juice, slowly blending in cherry juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the sauce is thick and clear.
Add the cherries. Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with the topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Contains 185 calories.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter large piece of foil first and spread on counter top. Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Melt together, then add peanuts and cook until color changes to pink.
Take off stove and add soda. Stir quickly.
Will foam immediately, then pour on foil.

title: how to bake a frozen turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wrap turkey breast in foil, using drugstore method of wrapping.
Place wrapped breast in aluminum baking pan.
Bake for 3 hours.
Remove from oven and carefully open top of foil, folding back.
Place margarine on top of turkey and season with salt and pepper.
Return to oven and bake an additional 30 minutes to brown.
Cool and slice.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring chicken, broth and water to a boil in a 4 to 5-quart pot.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add carrots, celery and onion.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer, until chicken is no longer pink near the bone.
Remove chicken.
Skim off all fat.
Stir in noodles, increase heat to medium and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender. Remove skin from chicken.
Tear meat into bite-size pieces.
Stir meat and parsley into soup.
Serves 6.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Saute ground beef with chopped pepper and onion.
Cook macaroni as box directs.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(This recipe freezes well.)

title: mini pizzas
directions: Spread about 2 tbsp. pasta sauce on each bread slice. Top with cheese. Place on microwave safe plate. Microwave on high 1 minute or until cheese is melted.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar.
Break eggs into a cup and then fill with milk to make 1 cup.
Add egg mixture to creamed mixture and stir until mixed.
Add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat until mixed.
Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a cookie sheet and bake at 375°.
Can be used to decorate for holidays.

title: punch(yellow)
directions: Mix all 3 juices together.
Mix sugar in warm water to dissolve.
Mix all together, then add ginger ale.

title: honey butter
directions: Let margarine soften, then place in food processor with honey and process until well blended.
Then process 1 minute more; chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Add broth and soup and vegetables. Let come to a boil.
Put in casserole.
Top with Bisquick crust rolled 1/4-inch thick.
Cut slits in crust and bake at 400° until brown.

title: no-peek chicken casserole
directions: Place washed rice in bottom of large baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover with combined soups and a cup of water.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and bake in a moderate oven.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in mixer.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
Allow to cool.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese until creamy; spread over cooled crust. Mix pudding, milk and vanilla; spread over cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate or nuts. Refrigerate.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; stir in butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and milk into a baking dish. Add cherries.
Put butter on top.
Place in oven and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie crust.
Preheat oven to 450°. Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 10 minutes longer.

title: yellow bird
directions: Put into blender with crushed ice.
Pour into a martini glass; top with a slice of lemon.
Serves 1.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and fruit juice; fold in fruit.
Put in a graham cracker crust; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mexicali burgers and rice
directions: In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch), combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled egg.
Sprinkle with additional chili powder if desired.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 clean flowerpot.

title: potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes in wedges, like boat shapes.
Roll each wedge in butter, with the skin on, and place it in a shallow pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and parsley.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and eggs (two at a time), mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and check.
May need to cook a little longer.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and continue to stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Add broth, water, soy sauce, garlic powder, chicken and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
(This can be frozen in a 1-gallon bag.)

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Combine Graham wafers crumbs, sugar into melted margarine; mix well and press evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan. Scatter chocolate chips over base. Spread coconut over chocolate chips, sprinkle pecans over coconut. Pour condensed milk over top, spread evenly. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares. Freezes nicely.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When thoroughly mixed, roll in small balls and press out with hands.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture on top of cookie and press down with hand.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, depending on your oven at 300° to 325° on the top rack of the oven.

title: hard salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours. Divide into 5 rolls, cracker size.
Bake on a rack in shallow pan 8 hours at 150°.
Cool and refrigerate or freeze.
Freezes well. Perfect with cheese and crackers.
Does not slice well until cold.

title: honey dinner rolls
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Heat margarine, milk and honey until warm and margarine is melted.
Add liquid to dry mixture and add eggs.
Knead and add flour to make dough smooth and elastic.
Put in well-greased bowl and allow to double, covered.
Make rolls and put in oiled muffin pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Use paper muffin cups to cut down on cleanup. Makes 36 rolls.

title: salmon cheese loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly, enough to fluff it up.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Add liquid from can of salmon.
Shape into loaf on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheese souffle sandwiches
directions: Butter a casserole.
Butter bread and make three layer sandwiches.
Place close together in dish.
Beat eggs and milk and rest of ingredients.
Pour over sandwiches.
Let stand 2 hours and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: You also need 12 cupcake papers.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Place sugar and Karo syrup in pan on low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until well blended. Remove pan from stove.
Pour over corn flakes.
Blend until well coated, but not crushed.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix together and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen very well.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together the pumpkin, Pet milk, eggs, sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Pour onto first baked mixture.
Combine the pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar and margarine; sprinkle pecan mixture over pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cocktail camaron sauce
directions: Mix altogether and pour over camarones (shrimp).

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture alternating with Hershey's syrup to creamed mixture.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add honey, salt, lemon juice and rind.
When it has congealed slightly, beat evaporated milk until stiff, then whip gelatin into it.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients and stuff chops with mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: carrot bread
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts, carrots and vanilla; blend quickly.
Pour into well greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach ice cream soda
directions: Mash the peach in bottom of a large glass with the sugar.
Add ice cream and the nectar.
Fill the glass with seltzer.
Serve with a tall spoon.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix cake and add 1/2 cup milk, nuts and butter.
Mix 1/2 of cake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Add chocolate chips and pour caramel over rest of cake on top.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Press out breast.
Top with 1/2 slice cheese and 2 pieces of dried beef.
Fold over and secure with toothpick.
Place in casserole.
Cover with sour cream and soup mixture.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Butter a baking sheet-keep warm.
Combine soda, 1 teaspoon water and vanilla; set aside.
Combine sugar, water and the corn syrup in large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 240° on a candy thermometer (or to the soft ball stage).
Stir in butter and pecans.

Cook, stirring constantly to 300° (or to crack stage). Immediately remove from heat: stir in soda mixture thoroughly; pour into warmed, buttered baking sheet and quickly spread evenly, as thin as possible.
Cool.
Break candy into pieces.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Spread berries in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour batter over berries and bake at 350 for 45 minutes until lightly brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening and salt to boiling water until melted.
Then add all flour and stir vigorously until all together, remove after heat.
Add egg, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Drop by spoon and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and then add filling.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Using a 9-inch glass baking dish, layer all ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6. Serve with salad and rye bread or toast sticks.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Blend in milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
In small mixing bowl add 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour water over top. Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dishes, using hot fudge sauce from the bottom of pan over top of cake.
Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and
shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Add alternately dry ingredients,
hot
water
and
soda.
Add
vanilla. Chill in refrigerator
overnight
if possible.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes (watch that
bottoms
do
not burn).
Store in tight container. Makes 5 to 7 dozen average cookies.

title: carrot candy
directions: In a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan, combine carrots and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a simmer over low heat.
Cover and cook slowly until soft, about 30 minutes.
With a potato masher, mash the carrots and any remaining liquid.
Stir in sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Return to a simmer over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until a thick paste forms, 50 to 60 minutes. Stir in ginger and cinnamon.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Make Jell-O with the hot water and cold water; add juice from pineapple.
Refrigerate until it congeals.
Whip the cream, but not too stiff, and fold in Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple and sugar.
Use a large bowl or mold.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat!
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt first four ingredients in double boiler.
Fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Flatten in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stir-fry chicken my way
directions: Marinate chicken breast in lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Or use any herbs you wish.
Marinate for at least 4 hours, overnight is better.
Then cut up chicken into 1-inch size.

title: punch
directions: Mix and chill the first 5 ingredients.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: filled cookies(use miniature pans)
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients except nuts.
Shape into a ball and sprinkle with chopped nuts or refrigerate after shaping to firm it and then roll in chopped nuts.

title: miss frances stephens' pineapple cake for a crowd
directions: Mix 3/4 cup undrained pineapple with coconut and set aside. Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Work shortening until soft, then add sugar until mixture is creamy. Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each one.
Mix flour mixture and remaining undrained pineapple into batter alternately. Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle batter with pineapple and coconut mixture and chocolate morsels.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° in greased pan.

title: tip's oyster dressing
directions: Brown ground beef, pork and turkey innards thoroughly for approximately 1/2 hour.
Saute the onions, shallots, garlic, celery and bell peppers.
Soak bread in oyster juice.
Squeeze and drain in colander.
Add to mixture.
Cook on low heat for several hours. Next morning, add oysters.
Add oyster juice according to texture.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Empty pineapple and juice in casserole dish, 8 x 12-inch or smaller.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple. Sprinkle cheese on this and then the crushed crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Delicious with ham.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings in a stockpot over very low heat for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Add green bell peppers. Cook until mixture is dark brown in color, stirring frequently.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Remove rolls from pan.
Slice them in half.
Put bottom half back in pan.
Mix seed, oleo and mustard.
Spread on top half of rolls.
Mix onion, ham and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on bottom half of rolls.
Cover with grated cheese.
Place top half back on bottom.
Slide tray back in plastic cover and freeze until needed. Thaw, wrap in foil and bake at 400° until cheese melts.
You may also break off two or three of the sandwiches, wrap in paper towel and microwave for about 30 seconds.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to boil and add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Mix well and add nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix honey and sugar in pan until it comes to a boil.
Stir. Blend in peanut butter.
Cool slightly.
Pour over popped corn and toss to coat evenly.
Butter hands and shape into balls.
Makes 1 dozen 3-inch balls.

title: ever ready muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients (except cereal) together in LARGE bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients (except cereal). Mix well. Add cereal. Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Saute garlic, pepper and onion in 1/4 cup oil until tender. Pour into mixing bowl. Add clams with juice, oregano, parsley, bread crumbs and lemon juice. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: instant cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: cranberry-pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for ginger ale.
Add the ginger ale to mixture in punch bowl.
A ring of pineapple juice in the punch bowl is a nice touch.
Purchase another can of pineapple juice.
Serves 25.

title: old fashioned white bread
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast into the warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast and 3 cups of flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Put into a greased bowl; turn once.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.

title: onions celeste
directions: Slice onions and saute in a large skillet with butter; sprinkle with pepper.
When onions are soft, place in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over onions and cheese.
Lay triangles of stale bread on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed; mix well.
Place in greased skillet.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls
and
press with fork. Bake at 350` for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Beat four minutes at medium speed.
Stir in pecans.
Spread batter evenly in a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Pie will puff, then fall slightly.

title: carrot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Combine pineapple, carrots, coconut, nuts and sugar.
Mix well.
Combine mayonnaise and reserved juice; beat well with a whisk until smooth.
Pour over carrot mixture, mix well and chill.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: great for all ages soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown ground beef. Break into small pieces. Drain.
Add other ingredients, except pasta. Bring to boil and add pasta.
Simmer until pasta is cooked.

title: hearty burgers
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into 6 patties and brown on both sides in large frying pan.
Pour soup over meat (add no water to soup). Top with green pepper. Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eclair pie(steph and sammy's favorite)
directions: Use a 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together. Make a layer of graham crackers, then half of cream mixture.
Make another layer of graham crackers, then 1/2 of cream mixture.
Layer more graham crackers and put milk chocolate icing on top.
Make 1 day ahead.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at
350° for 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat pizza
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with fork until smooth. Spread onto a 12 inch pizza pan to form a 10 inch circle leaving a 2 inch edge for crackers. Spread chili sauce on top of pizza. Garnish with fresh or dry parsley flakes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs with flour.
Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut up carrots and cook until tender. Marinate the other ingredients together.
Pour over carrots. Put in refrigerator.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine pecans, sugar, and salt; add egg whites and mix until completely damp mixture.
Form into small balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press hole in center of each ball; fill with preserves; Top with cherry (half).
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: not like mom makes toll house cookie recipe
directions: Put all ingredients into an industrial size mixer.
Mix ingredients until smooth.
Put cookies on well-greased floured sheets.
Bake until done.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, sugar, baking powder and poppy seed.
Make a well and add the oil, vanilla, eggs and orange juice.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Flatten balls onto a floured ungreased baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat
in skillet over medium heat.
Drain off fat and set
aside.
Blend
mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir
in
meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Turn into pastry
shell.
Bake
in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden
brown
on
top
and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and thinly slice about 15 pickles (do not peel).
Thinly slice 4 or 5 onions.
Place in a gallon jar.
Mix cold the remaining ingredients.
Pour over pickles and onions.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Do not seal.
Ready to eat in a couple of days.
As you use them, you can add more onions and pickles to the juice and mix.

title: punch bowl truffle
directions: Break pound cake into pieces in a large bowl, saving some of the cake for the top.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Slice 3 bananas on top of cherries.
Cover with instant pudding, mixed according to directions on box.
Then add the rest of the cake broken into pieces.
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut if desired.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Drain all fruit and layer in bowl.
Use juice from fruit and mix with pudding and pie filling to make 2 cups.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool slightly and pour over fruit in bowl.
Add bananas and toss lightly.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: tang tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.
To serve, put 2 heaping teaspoons in mug.
Fill with boiling water and stir.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine bananas, oranges and pineapple in bowl.
Mix Tang, pudding and pineapple juice together.
Stir real well.
Pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet; drain. Add tomatoes, spinach and 1/2 cup of the picante sauce, cumin and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in 1 cup of the cheese.
Heat about 1/2-inch oil in small skillet until hot.
Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds per side; drain on paper towels.
Spoon about 1/3 cup mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up and place, seam side down, in ungreased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Spoon remaining 1 1/4 cups picante sauce evenly over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and orange marmalade.
Stir in whipped topping.
Place a single layer of oranges on bottom of pie crust. Spoon cream cheese mixture over oranges.
Top with remaining oranges.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Serves 8.
Prep time:
10 minutes. Chill time:
2 hours or overnight.

title: red turner's rig cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon and set aside.
In saucepan, mix oleo, water and cocoa and bring to boil. Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir into cake mixture.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer about 30 minutes.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt and refrigerate two or more hours.
Drain off liquid and add vinegar and sugar.
Put in desired containers and freeze.
Makes about six pints.
Defrost and enjoy.

title: fig muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and corn syrup and mix well.
Blend in water, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and soda.
Add figs, mixing gently; stir in bread crumbs.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: easy shrimp (or crab) bisque
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and saute onion.
Add the sherry (or wine) and cook until the liquid reduces by half.
Add the soups, lemon juice and half and half, blending well.
Add shrimp (or crab).
Heat thoroughly by do not boil.	Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix and 1/3 cup milk with butter until it holds together.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk; set aside.
Put half of the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
