Pour caramel mixture over and sprinkle with chips.
Crumble remaining cake mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water until soft.
Add nondairy creamer, butter, green onion tops and bacon.
Simmer 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
(Add cheese after butter if you want potato cheese soup.) Can cut down on the water and add milk after the potatoes are done.
Mash the potatoes some after cooking for a smoother soup.

title: baby ruth
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into bars and freeze.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Boil for 30 minutes.
Puree ingredients.
Boil again for 20 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup sherry or white wine.
Add butter and mix well.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese and softened oleo.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 80 to 100 wafers.
Can freeze after baking.

title: old-fashioned pineapple rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Stir once during cook time. Will thicken as it cools.
Serve hot or cold.

title: friendship sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half approximately 3/16-inch thick on floured surface.
Using cookie cutter, cut shapes and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: human puppy chow
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose one too young and take only such varieties raised in a good moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and selected, let that part remain settled and give thought to preparations for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others constantly keep them in hot water.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat meat into bottom of casserole and place onion rings on top. Spread soup over onions, then layer of cheese. Completely cover with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry angel food cake dessert
directions: Using 1/2 of cake, pinch into little pieces in a large bowl. Mix pudding with milk and vanilla ice cream; mix with beaters real good.
Pour over top of cake; don't stir.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Put into a mixing bowl the first 7 ingredients.
Beat together about 4 minutes. Stir in the blackberries. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 8 x 12-inch pan for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chip dip
directions: In a cup, mix all ingredients, then use your favorite chip to dip.

title: lumberjack's stew
directions: Combine ingredients with 1 cup water.
Bring to slow boil, then simmer for about 2 or 3 hours.
Season to taste.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin into strips and coat with flour.
Heat skillet and add butter or oil.
When melted, brown beef.
Add mushrooms and onion, then add tomato sauce and beef broth.
Simmer for 1/2 hour to an hour.
For thicker sauce, simmer longer.
For thin sauce, add more liquids (equal parts).
Before serving add sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: kielbasa supper
directions: Cut kielbasa into bite size pieces.
Cut bacon into 2-inch pieces.
Place ingredients in large roaster or such in the following order:
Spread 1 can tomato soup on bottom of roaster. Sprinkle on sauerkraut.
Add 1 soup can of water.
Add sliced cabbage.
Add potatoes. Add onion, salt and pepper. Add carrots. Add kielbasa.
Add bacon. Spread on the second can of soup and pour 1 more can of water over all. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 25.

title: french fried cucumbers
directions: Pare and slice cucumbers in thin slices.
Salt lightly.
Dip in seasoned beaten egg, then dip in flour.
Fry in deep fat until brown on both sides.
Serve at once.
Very good.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop beef and onions (save enough beef to roll ball in).
Mix well all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: resurrection rolls
directions: A great Easter activity/story lesson for kids!
(Very tasty, too!)

title: pork roast barbecue
directions: Place roast, fat side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Insert meat thermometer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Put onto ungreased (or Pam) cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until they are slightly brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, shortening and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Then add eggs and mix.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together.
Add to margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Roll rounded teaspoonful size balls in 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water together.
Bring to a hard boil (240°).
Add peanuts, oleo and salt.
Cook until peanuts start bursting or 300°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda. Stir fast and empty into 8 or 9 buttered pans.
I use aluminum pie pans.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Break head of lettuce into pieces about 3-inch square.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from grease and stir into grease the mustard and add pickle juice.
Crumble bacon over lettuce and pour almost hot grease over lettuce and bacon.
Terrible for the arteries, but soooo good.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Garnish, if desired, and serve with tortilla chips. Yields 6 cups.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Measure flour and sift with salt.
Add shortening (at room temperature) and blend with pastry blender or two knives.
Add water.
Roll 1/8 inch thick and line pie pans.
Prick pastry and bake at 425 degrees for 12 to 15
minutes.
Yield:
Pastry for 2 (8-inch) pie crusts.

title: country ham balls
directions: Mix all together to make a stiff dough. Oops! First chop country ham in food processor. To make dough, hands work best. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: tomato and scallop chowder
directions: Heat oil in a large deep saucepan.
Add onion and celery; cook until the vegetables are soft, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, bay leaf and basil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add water, clam juice and scallops.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Season to taste with pepper and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: friendship bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water, then feed it 1 cup warm water, 2/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons potato flakes.
Let this mixture set out all day, then refrigerate for 2 to 5 days.
Take it out and feed again with remaining 1 cup water, 2/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons potato flakes.
Let set out all day or overnight.
Now, you are ready to use 1 cup of the Starter to make your first batch of bread.
The rest goes back into the refrigerator to be used and the process repeated in 2 to 5 days.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole or mixing bowl.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave 2 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 and 4 minutes until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness and cool on well buttered cookie sheet.

title: taco pot pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add 1 package of taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Simmer until liquid is thick.
Add 1/2 of beans to each pie shell.
Add 1/2 meat mixture to each shell.
Spread with shredded cheese.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and light brown.
Remove.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Layer casserole dish with 1/2 can peas, 1/2 can mushroom soup and top with pats of margarine.
Bake at 350° until soup becomes bubbly.
Add French fried onions as a topper.
Place back into oven.
Broil until desired brownness.
Great side dish.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients using enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaf with cheese crackers or other choice.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Crush the Ritz crackers.
Save 1/4 cup for spreading on top. Melt oleo and mix with the cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt yogurt or ice cream.
Mix pudding with the yogurt or ice cream.
Spread over the crust and top with Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 cup of crackers on top.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: plantation cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese and dry vanilla pudding together well. Drain the fruit cocktail well on paper towels and add to the cream cheese mixture.
Shape into a ball (or mound if on a flat plate) and pat the nuts on top.
Serve with Wheat Thin crackers.
ENJOY!!

title: coffee can ice cream
directions: You will also need a 1 pound and a 3 pound coffee can.

title: basic omelet
directions: In a 9 or 10-inch skillet or omelet pan, melt margarine over medium-high heat, tilting pan to coat bottom.
In small bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper until combined; pour into skillet. Reduce heat to low and cook without stirring.
As edges set, lift edges to allow the uncooked egg to flow to bottom of pan, tilting pan as necessary.
Cook until mixture is set, but top is still moist looking.
Add any desired filling to omelet.
With spatula, loosen edge of omelet and fold in half as omelet slides from pan to serving platter.
Yield: 2 to 3 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, oil, cocoa and water to a rapid boil; remove from heat and add vanilla.
In a large mixer bowl, sift flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Pour warm mixture over top and blend.
Add 2 beaten eggs and 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Beat well and pour into well-oiled 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix warm water and
yeast in a large bowl.
Add lukewarm water mixture, egg and half of flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough of remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Place dough in large bowl and refrigerate.
(Can be stored for 1 week.) Punch down.
Pinch off small amounts; roll into balls and place in greased pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar. Add rest of ingredients. Coat fruit and nuts with 1/2 of the flour. Put other 1/2 in batter (add a little pumpkin pie spice to flour, if desired). Mix all together and drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yield: 250 cookies.

title: peanut butter and jelly jewels
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine sugars in large mixer bowl.
Add peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add egg and extract; mix well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Refrigerate covered at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place on unbuttered cookie sheets 1 1/2 inches apart.
Use handle of wooden spoon to make deep indentions in center of each ball. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Cool on cookie sheets until firm enough to lift.
Transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
Fill centers with cherry preserves or glace cherries.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and
cut
sweet
potatoes	in small pieces.
Cover with water
and	cook
until tender.
Put potatoes, butter and sugar in a
mixing
bowl. Beat until smooth.
Add milk and mix well.
Add flavorings	and
spices.
Remove
"strings"
that accumulate on beaters.
Mix
in
flour
and
blend.
Add	egg yolks.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour in unbaked pie crusts.	Beat egg whites on high
until soft peaks form.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Put
meringue on pies and bake at 350° until meringue is brown and pie is set.

title: lumberjack salad
directions: Cut pimento, pepper, celery and onion up fine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add vanilla pudding to juice.
Stir until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Just before serving, add bananas.
Refrigerate and serve cool.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in olive oil until tender.
Add potatoes and cover with boiling water.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook ten minutes. Then add cubed fish.
When all is cooked, add evaporated milk and heat through.
Add butter and sprinkle paprika on top.
Serve with crackers and salad.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 5 tablespoons sugar and melted oleo and pour over mixture.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar and juices. Prepare rest of veggies and fruit; then add to jello and refrigerate until firm.

title: macaroni and chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve well chilled.

title: pudding-wiches
directions: Gradually add milk to peanut butter in a deep narrow bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at lowest speed of mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spread filling 1/2-inch thick on 12 graham crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 350° oven until golden brown and set.

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Saute almonds in butter until lightly browned.
Add lemon and pepper seasoning salt.
Toss almonds with green beans.

title: amaretto slush
directions: Freeze overnight, stirring occasionally.
Scoop mixture into glass and mix with Seven-Up (1:1 concentration).
Stays good in freezer for months.
Excellent!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in some butter.
Add soup and cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Cook rice and broccoli as directed on packages.
Stir rice in cheese mixture.
Put broccoli (already cooked) in casserole dish.
Add cheese mixture to broccoli.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry squares(serves 12)
directions: Stir together first four ingredients.
Remove 1/3 of this mixture and reserve.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally, until light brown.

title: hot wassail
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large kettle and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cuban chickpeas and chorizo (portuguese sausage)
directions: In large skillet, over low heat, heat the oil.
Then add the onion, pepper and garlic, stirring until tender, 6 to 8 minutes. Add the tomatoes, chicken broth, oregano, basil, cumin and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until heated through.
Add the chickpeas, chorizo and ham.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour.

title: cranberry delight spread
directions: I add 1 tablespoon sour cream.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: In a food processor, grind cranberries, oranges, apples, and celery together.
Place in a bowl, mix in the sugar and allow it to rest while preparing the jello, but only using the hot water. Allow jello to cool but not thicken, mix in the fruit. Refrigerate, mold if desired.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9x13 in. greased and floured pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: clam lovers clam dip
directions: Gently fold clams into sour cream. Add other ingredients and stir gently until blended.
Serve with chips.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Grease baking dish with oil. Put corn into dish.
Break in eggs and stir until mixed.
Pour in milk.
While stirring, add sugar, salt and sprinkle top with dry bread crumbs and paprika. Pepper may be chopped up into corn, if desired.
Put dish in pan of hot water and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cheddar-broccoli scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato.
Microwave on medium/low for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir and let stand covered for 2 minutes. Microwave an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are done. Serve atop tomato slices.
Yields 2 to 3 portions.

title: calico cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on low heat until done. Do not add any liquid. Stir frequently.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Place margarine in a 9x13 in. pan and place in oven to melt.
When margarine melts, pour into a mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients, and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and garlic in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Combine next 3 ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Add soup mix, peppers and pimento and set aside.
Soften tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil, draining on paper towel.
Add Cheddar cheese and onions to cooled ground beef mixture.
Fill tortillas with ground beef mixture.
Roll to enclose filling.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over enchiladas.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asian eggplant dip
directions: Cut off eggplant stem. Rinse.
Pierce eggplant in 12 places with a fork.
Set in baking pan at 350° for 1 hour in oven until sagging.
Cool and peel.
Put everything in blender. Serve at room temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and soda in milk.
Sift in flour and salt alternately with mashed bananas.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and beat with a whisk until mixed together well.
Marinate your favorite steak, London broil or chicken for several hours.
Bake, broil or barbecue.
Enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash, chopped onion and salt together until tender and drain.
Add the soup, sour cream, water chestnuts and grated carrots.
In a separate bowl, put 1 stick of melted butter and mix with the herb dressing mix.
Then put 1/2 of the dressing in the bottom of the baking dish.
Add the squash mixture.
Cover the top of the squash mixture with the remaining herb dressing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be divided into 2 casseroles, freeze 1 and/or take 1 to a friend.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine together and bake at 250° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together and cut 1 stick oleo on top.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir while baking, then sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, salt and boiling water well to dissolve grease.
Add warm water and yeast.
Then add the eggs.
Put in plain flour one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Leave in same bowl. Put some oil on top of dough.
Put Saran Wrap over bowl.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Make out amount you need.
Dot with butter.
Let rise in warmest place you have for 2 or 3 hours or until they rise.
Bake at 400° until done.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks or longer.
Makes 45 rolls.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: whole wheat bran bread
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 cup water and milk.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in cereal, butter, molasses, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Heat remaining water to 110° to 115° and pour into large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle with yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add cereal mixture and whole wheat flour.
Beat well. Add enough all-purpose flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch the dough down.
Shape into two loaves and place in greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 2 loaves.
If cooking for two, wrap one loaf in heavy-duty aluminum foil and freeze to enjoy later.

title: orange roughy with peppers
directions: Put orange roughy in greased baking pan.
Melt butter and add garlic.
Baste roughy with garlic-butter and lemon juice. Sprinkle with lemon pepper, seasoning salt and paprika.
Layer with green, red and yellow peppers.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in 4 tablespoons of boiling water.
Stir into applesauce.
Cream together sugar, salt, margarine, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat all together.
Add this to flour and raisins.
(Use tube pan.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan party log
directions: Blend the first three ingredients.
Add the peppers and pimento and mix well.
Form
into
log.
Wrap
in waxed paper. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Remove paper.	Roll in chopped parsley.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sweetened condensed milk until thoroughly blended together.
Then add Cool Whip and mix until thoroughly blended together.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and smooth out into pie crust.	Cut desired fruit (optional) and arrange on top of mixture.	Let it set in the refrigerator for at least one hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add well beaten eggs, vanilla, syrup and salt.
Add pecans and flour.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.
To keep top from burning, cover with buttered foil.
Make sure pie shell has no holes in it.

title: taco soup(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook together for about an hour.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Add to mix a little at a time until mixed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and pepper in butter.
Mix eggs, corn and muffin mix.
Pour this into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spoon sauteed mixture over top of corn mixture.
Cover with grated sharp cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until firm in center.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems and saute in margarine with the onions.
Add crumbs, cheese, parsley, lemon juice and salt.
Mix all together.
Fill mushroom caps and place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 8 minutes at 450° until slightly brown.
Serve hot.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Combine the sugar, cornstarch, salt and oil.
Add the Karo syrup and water.
Stir until the mixture boils rapidly.
Cook to 252° or until a little in cold water forms a fairly firm ball. Flavor and pour onto a large oiled platter.
When cool enough to handle, oiling hands with a little oil, pull into rope and cut in 1 inch pieces.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in casserole dish in microwave until almost done.
Drain water.
Add soup, salt and pepper and mix well. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, pepper and water to a good boil.
Mix all vegetables together.
Pour boiled mixture over vegetables and stir to mix.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator in glass or plastic container.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In medium pan, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Mix in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly to keep mixture smooth.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes.
Cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: sue's surprise pudding cake
directions: Beat.
Spread on crust.
Add remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until done. Cool in pan or rack for 10 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: divinity
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Microwave at High for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 8 to 12 minutes or until mixture reaches hard ball stage (260°). Immediately beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites, beating at high speed with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture holds its shape and starts to lose its gloss.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Quickly drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or spread into a lightly buttered 6 x 10-inch dish and cut into pieces.

title: w w breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake crust according to package directions for prebaked shell.
Cool completely.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Place half the cheese in baked shell.
Top with sausage, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
In medium bowl whisk eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over filled pie shell.
Bake at 450° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Each serving provides 2 protein, 1 bread and 125 optional calories; 213 calories and 9 grams fat per serving.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In a large pan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Add onion and celery.
Saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, molasses, mustard and salt.
Heat to boiling point.
Add shredded cabbage.
Stir to mix.
Cover and simmer until very tender, about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add other ingredients. Add remaining 1/2 can of soup on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and	milk
with a fork until creamy. Add other ingredients, then stir in sour cream.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake
at
for	15
to	20 minutes. Serve with crackers.
Serves
to
Doubled
it serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh peach pie glaze
directions: Mix peach Jell-O, sugar and clear jell.
Add this to hot water.
Bring to a boil and let cook 1/2 minute.
This should be real thick.
Cool.

title: baked chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with beef slices and place chicken on beef.
Mix soup with sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil until last 1/2 hour of baking.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat chicken broth, salt and white pepper to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir green onion into eggs.
Pour egg mixture slowly into broth, stirring constantly with fork until egg forms shreds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls;
press
with
fork on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kindergarten applesauce cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, apple pie spice, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl at medium speed, beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy. Beat in applesauce, corn syrup and egg.
On low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture. Divide dough into four portions.
Wrap each portion in plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Chill several hours until firm enough to roll.
Turn oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets or spray with nonstick coating.

On a lightly floured surface, roll one portion of the dough at a time into a 1/4-inch thick circle. Dip cutter into flour before cutting each cookie. Place cookies about 1-inch apart on cookie sheets. For soft cookies, bake 8 to 10 minutes. For crisp cookies, bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Use hot pads to carefully remove cookie sheets from oven.
Remove cookies from cookie sheets and cool on wire cooling racks.
Makes 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: ham-rice timbales
directions: Combine ham, rice, egg yolks, mayonnaise and dry mustard. Shape approximately 1/2 cup of mixture for each cone.
Dip in egg whites and roll in cornflake crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top each slice with ham cone.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Heat soup and serve 1/4 cup of mixture over each cone. Yields 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Combine with sugar and pretzels. Stir together and bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Remove, stir and cool.
Using mixer, combine cream cheese with sugar, into this fold Cool Whip and pineapple.
Mix all together including cooled mixture of pretzels.
Chill before serving.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in a medium saucepan. Boil 3 minutes. Stir in cocoa and oatmeal, vanilla and nuts or coconut. Beat well.
Working quickly, drop by spoonful onto waxed paper. Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put beans in bottom of serving dish.
Peel and mash the avocados.
Mix with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Spread avocado mixture over beans.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocado mixture.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture.
Beat until well combined.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Cool about 1 minute before removing to a wire rack.

title: pickled cocktail mushrooms
directions: Combine vinegar, seasonings and mushroom liquor.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Turn into a jar; let stand overnight.
Letting them stand 1 to 2 weeks will improve flavor.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Mix together the marshmallow cream and the soft cream cheese. Scoop into a small bowl and place in the center of a beautiful fresh fruit tray.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese.
Toss bread crumbs in butter and put on top of casserole.
Top with sharp grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: egg and sausage bake
directions: Cook crumbled sausage well done and drain.
Combine eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard
in bowl.
Set aside.
Place croutons in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sausage.
Pour egg mixture over sausage and croutons.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour until firm in center and brown on top.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
In a bowl, lightly beat eggs and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
Shake off excess.
Shake a few chicken pieces in the bag at a time, coating well.
In electric skillet, heat oil to 350°.
Brown chicken on all sides.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out excess liquid. Combine all ingredients. Pour into 1-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done. Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer ground beef, potato slices and chopped onion.
Pour cream of celery soup over top.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: hamburger rice
directions: Brown hamburger with celery and onion.
Combine water, rice and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Let stand.
Add soy sauce and brown sugar to hamburger mixture.
Add soup mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour and salt; beat well.
Add syrup, milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour pecans in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top cracks open and is golden brown.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Put crushed chips in a 9 x 9-inch casserole, greased.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix soup, milk and seasoning.
Add meat and onion to soup mix and spoon over chips.
Sprinkle lettuce and tomatoes on top.
Then add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce and sour cream.
Very good!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix
flour,
butter,
nuts,
vanilla and 5 teaspoons 10x sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan (thin layer).
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix 1 1/4 cups 10x sugar, creamed cheese and 1 small Cool Whip and put on top of 1st layer. Mix
pudding mix and cold milk and put on top of 2nd layer.
Put Cool Whip for 4th layer on 3rd layer.
Sprinkle nuts
on Cool Whip.
You	may
garnish
top
with
shavings
of Hershey's chocolate candy bar.
Chill well before cutting.

title: fried asparagus
directions: Take the water out of asparagus and let set for a few minutes.
Then take each piece of asparagus and dip in beaten eggs.
Then take a piece of waxed paper with crushed crackers on it and roll each piece of asparagus with the crumbs and put in buttered frying pan (hot).
Cook until crisp on both sides.
Salt and flavor to your taste.

title: festive winter crunch bar
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line bar pan with 2 (16-inch) pieces of parchment paper, allowing about 6-inches to extend over the sides of pan. In 2-quart saucepan, add 1-inch of water to a simmer over medium heat. Coarsely chop almond bark and place in double boiler. Set double boiler over simmering water in saucepan. Melt bark 12 to 15 minutes or until melted, stirring occasionally.

title: orange chicken(good!)
directions: Lightly pound chicken to help prevent shrinkage.
Dip each breast in egg white, then in bread crumbs, coating evenly.
In a large skillet, heat oil and saute each breaded breast over medium heat until golden. Clean skillet.

In it combine orange juice, marmalade, lemon juice, lemon zest, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth. Add chicken. Cover and cook 10 more minutes or until tender.
Contains 73 mg cholesterol and 397 calories.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Melt butter and saute onions.
Add seasonings, mushroom liquid, and blend in soup. Gradually add milk and stir until smooth and thickened.
In a large bowl, mix cooked rice, mushrooms, pimento and chicken that has been chopped into small pieces.
Blend in sauce.
Pour into lightly buttered casserole.
Top with 2 cheeses.
Garnish with whole mushrooms and pimento strips, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until tender. In another saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually add milk and sour cream. Bring to a boil. Stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Drain potatoes. Add cream sauce. Toss gently. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and 1 onion until browned.
Drain.
Add taco mix and beans.
Chop all remaining vegetables and keep separate. When ready to serve, add salsa, vegetables and cheese.
Mix well. Add Fritos the very last.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Mixture can be frozen.
If this is done, leave rice out until baking time.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften. Mix all ingredients together with cream cheese. When well mixed, add shrimp and stir well. Chill until ready to serve.

title: coconut pyramids
directions: Separate egg yolks.
Put in a bowl (for later).
In large bowl mix coconut, sugar and egg whites until fairly stiff.
With small egg cup press in mixture.
Turn out pyramids onto baking pan and continue until all mixture is used.
Beat together egg yolks and baste gently on top of pyramids.
Bake at 250° to 300° until slightly brown.

title: creamy no cook sauce(for fresh fruit)
directions: Beat all ingredients together until blended; cover and chill. At serving time, fill dessert glasses with fresh fruit and top with chilled sauce.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar; add 3 tablespoons milk.
Add other ingredients until soft, then add salt.
Take fruits and nuts; add 1 cup flour.
Mix until each piece is covered with flour.
Add to liquid mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375°.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream margarine and cheese until smooth.
Add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cake with crushed pecans.

title: "luck of the irish" bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool; cover with foil until ready to serve.
Happy St. Patrick's Day!

title: san jacinto inn biscuits
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk and work with hands on lightly floured board. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Cook at 400° to 425° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 20 large biscuits.

title: dessert orange balls
directions: Mix thawed but still slushy juice together with ingredients, except powdered sugar. Stir until smooth, adding the sifted powdered sugar, a little at a time.

Refrigerate the dough for 15 to 20 minutes. This allows tiny 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch balls to be rolled by pinching a bit of dough off and rolling on waxed paper. Roll the balls in powdered sugar and freeze in a container a couple of hours before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in eggs and beat well.
Make a paste of the vinegar and cocoa.
Add to the creamed mixture. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk. Mix in the vanilla and red food coloring.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Spread chicken in 12 x 14-inch sprayed pan.
Put on next 3 items.
Mix next 3 items.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown in 400° oven.

title: homemade red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Make a paste of coloring and cocoa. Add and mix. Combine buttermilk with vanilla and add alternately with the flour combined with salt. Add soda and vinegar. Mix well. Cook 30 minutes at 350° in two 9-inch pans. When cool, split layers to make 4 layers.

title: mama's martha washington cake
directions: You may make your own angel food cake or buy one from the grocery.
Split cake into three layers.
Mix ingredients for icing: cheese, Cool Whip and sugars.
Ice each layer and spoon cherry filling in between each layer.
Top with remaining pie filling and drizzle juice down side of cake.
Refrigerate for at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: "can do" chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch, or 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend on low speed 30 seconds, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake layers 30 to 35 minutes, oblong 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Frost as desired.

title: incredible chicken
directions: Place 5 pieces of bacon on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Sprinkle 1 cup raw rice (Uncle Ben's) on top.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Mix 1 cup cream of mushroom soup with 1 can water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Seal with foil.
Cook 2 hours at 300°.
Do not peek.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine chuck, crumbs, egg, milk and salt and 1/2 package of spaghetti sauce mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into walnut size balls and place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Blend remaining sauce mix and gravy; pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over hot, buttered noodles.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In muffin pan lined with paper baking cups, fill 1/3 full of chocolate batter.
Top each cup with a heaping tsp. of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped blanched almonds if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: famed fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Add eggs.
Blend into mixture.
Chop fruit and nuts.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with baking powder.
Mix flour with fruit and nuts.
Fold flour mixture into butter mixture.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Pour into a greased, paper-lined tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes a 5-pound cake.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and add onions, peppers, radishes and tomatoes. Mix with dressing. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: spice applesauce cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: farm-style oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, lard, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in water.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: spaghetti squash salad
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Fill pan with hot water to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
When cool enough to handle, scoop out the squash, separating the strands with a fork.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; add squash and stir well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon as a salad or as a relish with hamburgs or hot dogs.
Store in the refrigerator.
Serving Size:

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses well, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pinch off. Roll about the size of a small walnut. Roll in sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet. Do not press; they will flatten out as they cook. Heat oven to 350°. Cook for 10 minutes. DO NOT OVERCOOK.
